AddressDim.description: The address dimension contains information about addresses. Each row represents an address.  This dimension can also contain standardized addresses, latitudes, and longitudes if your organization sends the source addresses to third party software.

columns.name: AddressKey
columns.description: Surrogate key used to uniquely identify the record

columns.name: DeidLds
columns.description: Shows 'DEID' if this is de-identified data and 'LDS' if this is a Limited Data Set

columns.name: SourceAddress
columns.description: Street address extracted from a source system

columns.name: SourceCity
columns.description: City extracted from a source system

columns.name: SourceCounty
columns.description: County extracted from a source system

columns.name: SourceStateOrProvince
columns.description: State or province extracted from a source system

columns.name: SourceCountry
columns.description: Country extracted from a source system

columns.name: SourcePostalCode
columns.description: Postal code extracted from a source system

columns.name: Address
columns.description: Street address. By default, this is the same as the street address extracted from the source system.

columns.name: City
columns.description: City. By default, this is the same as the city extracted from the source system.

columns.name: County
columns.description: County. By default, this is the same as the county extracted from the source system.

columns.name: StateOrProvince
columns.description: State or province. By default, this is the same as the state or province extracted from the source system.

columns.name: Country
columns.description: Country. By default, this is the same as the country extracted from the source system.

columns.name: PostalCode
columns.description: Postal code. By default, this is the same as the postal code extracted from the source system.

columns.name: Latitude
columns.description: Latitude

columns.name: Longitude
columns.description: Longitude

columns.name: Status
columns.description: Indicates whether the address has been standardized and validated

AllergenDim.description: The allergen dimension contains information about allergens. Each row represents an allergen.  For Epic data, this dimension also contains a row that corresponds to the no known allergies status.

columns.name: AllergenKey
columns.description: Surrogate key used to uniquely identify the record

columns.name: DeidLds
columns.description: Shows 'DEID' if this is de-identified data and 'LDS' if this is a Limited Data Set

columns.name: AllergenEpicId
columns.description: Epic ID of the allergen. This column identifies allergen (ELG) records.

columns.name: Name
columns.description: Name of the allergen

columns.name: Type
columns.description: Type of the allergen

AllergyFact.description: The allergy fact contains information about allergies. Each row represents an allergy for a patient.  For Epic data, this fact also contains records for patients with no known allergies.; NOTE: 6/19/2014 TAS: When an allergy record is deleted in LPL, a reason for deletion is chosen by the user.  That reason is stored in ALLERGY.ALRGY_DLET_RSN_C and links to the ZC_ALRGY_DLET_RSN category table.   6/16/2014 TAS: Clarity ALLERGY count for Active Allergies matches the Warehouse count for AllergyFact.  Clarity's category column ALRGY_STATUS_C in ALLERGY can be either 1 (Active) or 2 (Deleted).

columns.name: AllergyKey
columns.description: Surrogate key used to uniquely identify the record

columns.name: DeidLds
columns.description: Shows 'DEID' if this is de-identified data and 'LDS' if this is a Limited Data Set

columns.name: PatientDurableKey
columns.description: This is the de-identified version of PatientDim.DurableKey.  There is one value per person. Use this to join to the same patient in other tables, or to re-identify the patient at a later date with IRB approval

columns.name: PatientKey
columns.description: Patient associated with the allergy or the no known allergies status

columns.name: AllergenKey
columns.description: Allergen associated with the allergy or the no known allergies status

columns.name: StartDateKey
columns.description: Date when the allergy started or the no known allergies status was added. For Epic data, this column stores the noted date if it is available.  Otherwise it stores the date when the allergy or the no known allergies status was documented.

columns.name: AllergenName
columns.description: Name of the allergen; AllergenName comes from table AllergenDim, column Name by joining on key AllergenKey

columns.name: AllergenType
columns.description: Type of the allergen; AllergenType comes from table AllergenDim, column Type by joining on key AllergenKey

columns.name: EndDateKey
columns.description: Date when the allergy ended or the no known allergies status was removed. For Epic data, this column stores the deletion date or the expiration date of the allergy or the no known allergies status.

columns.name: LastReviewedDateKey
columns.description: Most recent date the allergy or the no known allergies status was reviewed or when an inability to review the allergy or the no known allergies status was indicated

columns.name: LastReviewedByEmployeeKey
columns.description: Employee who most recently reviewed the allergy or the no known allergies status or indicated an inability to review the allergy or the no known allergies status

columns.name: StartDateKeyValue
columns.description: Date when the allergy started or the no known allergies status was added. For Epic data, this column stores the noted date if it is available.  Otherwise it stores the date when the allergy or the no known allergies status was documented.; StartDateKeyValue is the natural value of StartDateKey that you can see without any key decoding

columns.name: EndDateKeyValue
columns.description: Date when the allergy ended or the no known allergies status was removed. For Epic data, this column stores the deletion date or the expiration date of the allergy or the no known allergies status.; EndDateKeyValue is the natural value of EndDateKey that you can see without any key decoding

columns.name: DocumentedByEmployeeKey
columns.description: Employee who originally documented the allergy or the no known allergies status

columns.name: LastReviewedDateKeyValue
columns.description: Most recent date the allergy or the no known allergies status was reviewed or when an inability to review the allergy or the no known allergies status was indicated; LastReviewedDateKeyValue is the natural value of LastReviewedDateKey that you can see without any key decoding

columns.name: Type
columns.description: Type of the allergy

columns.name: Severity
columns.description: Severity of the allergy

columns.name: Status
columns.description: Status of the allergy or the no known allergies status. This column stores Expired if it still stores Active when the extraction date is past the end date.

columns.name: FirstReaction
columns.description: First reaction associated with the allergy

columns.name: SecondReaction
columns.description: Second reaction associated with the allergy

columns.name: ThirdReaction
columns.description: Third reaction associated with the allergy

columns.name: Count
columns.description: Artificial measure on which calculations can be done. The value is 0 for rows marked as deleted, 1 otherwise.

AnesthesiaMetricValueFact.description: The anesthesia custom metric value fact contains information about custom metrics added to the Anesthesia and Perfusion Record registries. Each row represents a metric value.

AnesthesiaRecordAttributeValueDim.description: The anesthesia record attribute value dimension contains information about values of additional attributes for the anesthesia record fact. Each row represents an attribute value for an anesthesia record encounter.   For Epic data, the fact includes SmartData element values with encounter contexts unless the data type is Element ID or Image.

columns.name: AnesthesiaRecordAttributeValueKey
columns.description: Surrogate key used to uniquely identify the record

columns.name: AnesthesiaRecordKey
columns.description: Anesthesia record associated with the attribute value

columns.name: AttributeKey
columns.description: Attribute associated with the value

columns.name: OrderKey
columns.description: The order associated with the attribute value

columns.name: ProviderKey
columns.description: For attribute values which network to an Epic provider record, the provider documented

columns.name: ProviderDurableKey
columns.description: For attribute values which network to an Epic provider record, the provider documented

columns.name: ProviderSourceDataDurableKey
columns.description: For attribute values which network to an Epic provider record, the provider documented

columns.name: NoteKey
columns.description: The clinical note in which the attribute value was documented

columns.name: DateKey
columns.description: Date associated with the attribute value

columns.name: DateValue
columns.description: Value of the attribute in date format

columns.name: NumericValue
columns.description: Value of the attribute in numeric format

columns.name: StringValue
columns.description: Value of the attribute in string format

columns.name: NoteType
columns.description: The note type in which the attribute value was documented, if applicable

columns.name: Context
columns.description: Where the attribute value was documented

columns.name: _IsInferred
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the record is inferred

columns.name: _IsDeleted
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the record is deleted

AnesthesiaRecordFact.description: The anesthesia record fact contains information about anesthesia records. Each row represents an anesthesia record.

columns.name: AnesthesiaRecordKey
columns.description: Surrogate key used to uniquely identify the record

columns.name: AnesthesiaRecordEpicId
columns.description: Epic ID of the anesthesia record. This column identifies summary block (HSB) records.

columns.name: PatientKey
columns.description: Patient associated with the record

columns.name: PatientSourceDataDurableKey
columns.description: Patient associated with the record

columns.name: SurgicalCaseKey
columns.description: Primary surgical case associated with the anesthesia record

columns.name: AnesthesiaDayOfSurgeryEncounterKey
columns.description: Encounter containing day of surgery data for the anesthesia record. For Epic data, this is the type 52 encounter.

columns.name: AnesthesiaNoteEncounterKey
columns.description: Encounter containing note data and other data that applies to the entire anesthesia episode. For Epic data, this is the type 53 encounter.

columns.name: HospitalEncounterKey
columns.description: Encounter associated with the hospital admission or hospital outpatient visit with which the case is associated

columns.name: AnesthesiaRegistryMetricKey
columns.description: For Epic data, the registry record containing data for Anesthesia registry metrics

columns.name: AgeKey
columns.description: Patient age as of the date of anesthesia. This is calculated based on the AnesthesiaDateKey and the BirthDate column in PatientDim.

columns.name: ResponsibleAnesthesiologistKey
columns.description: Responsible provider for the record

columns.name: ResponsibleAnesthesiologistSourceDataDurableKey
columns.description: Responsible provider for the record

columns.name: PrimarySurgeonKey
columns.description: Primary surgeon for the record

columns.name: PrimarySurgeonSourceDataDurableKey
columns.description: Primary surgeon for the record

columns.name: PrimaryProcedureKey
columns.description: Primary procedure associated with the record

columns.name: PrimaryProcedureDurableKey
columns.description: Primary procedure associated with the record

columns.name: DepartmentKey
columns.description: Department in which the anesthesia procedure was performed

columns.name: OperatingRoomKey
columns.description: Operating room in which the procedure took place

columns.name: AnesthesiaDateKey
columns.description: Date of the anesthesia record

columns.name: AnesthesiaStartDateKey
columns.description: Date when anesthesia began for the patient. For Epic data, this is the date of the anesthesia start event.

columns.name: AnesthesiaStartTimeOfDayKey
columns.description: Time of day when anesthesia began for the patient. For Epic data, this is the time of day of the anesthesia start event.

columns.name: AnesthesiaStartInstant
columns.description: Date and time that anesthesia started for the patient. For Epic data, this is the instant of the anesthesia start event.

columns.name: AnesthesiaEndDateKey
columns.description: Date when anesthesia ended for the patient. For Epic data, this is the date of the anesthesia end event.

columns.name: AnesthesiaEndTimeOfDayKey
columns.description: Time of day when anesthesia ended for the patient. For Epic data, this is the time of day of the anesthesia end event.

columns.name: AnesthesiaEndInstant
columns.description: Date and time that anesthesia ended for the patient. For Epic data, this is the instant of the anesthesia end event.

columns.name: PreprocedureDiagnosisComboKey
columns.description: All preprocedure diagnoses for the anesthesia record

columns.name: PrimaryProcedureName
columns.description: Primary procedure name associated with the anesthesia record. This can contain the surgical procedure, procedure appointment, or ad hoc procedure.

columns.name: FirstAnesthesiaType
columns.description: First anesthesia type

columns.name: SecondAnesthesiaType
columns.description: Second anesthesia type

columns.name: ThirdAnesthesiaType
columns.description: Third anesthesia type

columns.name: SurgicalService
columns.description: Surgical service of the primary procedure associated with the anesthesia record

columns.name: PrimaryAnesthesiaType
columns.description: Primary anesthesia type

columns.name: AdmissionPatientClass
columns.description: Patient class at the time of admission

columns.name: AsaPhysicalStatus
columns.description: American Society of Anesthesiologists (ASA) physical status classification

columns.name: AnesthesiaProviderGroup
columns.description: The provider group associated with the responsible anesthesiologist on the record

columns.name: IsEmergent
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating if the anesthesia procedure was emergent. This column returns 1 if the procedure was emergent or 0 if it was not.

columns.name: IsAdHocProcedure
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating if the procedure was an ad hoc procedure. This column returns 1 if the procedure was an ad hoc procedure or 0 if it was not.

columns.name: IsUnsuccessfulAttempt
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates if the anesthesia record was associated with an unsuccessful attempt case. This column returns 1 if the anesthesia record was associated with an unsuccessful case and 0 otherwise.

columns.name: Count
columns.description: Artificial measure on which calculations can be done. The value is 0 for rows marked as deleted, 1 otherwise.

columns.name: _IsInferred
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the record is inferred

columns.name: _IsDeleted
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the record is deleted

columns.name: PreprocedureDiagnosisComboIdTypeId
columns.description: The IdTypeId corresponding to the DiagnosisBridge lookup

columns.name: PreprocedureDiagnosisComboId
columns.description: The Id corresponding to the DiagnosisBridge lookup

AnesthesiaRegistryMetricFact.description: The anesthesia registry metric fact contains information about anesthesia records. Each row represents an anesthesia record.

columns.name: AnesthesiaRegistryMetricKey
columns.description: Surrogate key used to uniquely identify the record

columns.name: ProcedureStartDateKey

columns.name: ProcedureStartInstant

columns.name: ProcedureEndDateKey
columns.description: This column should no longer be used and will be removed in a future version. Please use the corresponding column in AnesthesiaRecordFact.  Date when the procedure ended, or when the incision was closed

columns.name: ProcedureEndInstant
columns.description: This column should no longer be used and will be removed in a future version. Please use the corresponding column in AnesthesiaRecordFact.  Date and time when the procedure ended, or when the incision was closed

columns.name: PatientInRoomDateKey
columns.description: This column should no longer be used and will be removed in a future version. Please use the corresponding column in AnesthesiaRecordFact.  Date when the patient arrived in the operating room

columns.name: PatientOutOfRoomDateKey

columns.description: This column should no longer be used and will be removed in a future version. Please use the corresponding column in AnesthesiaRecordFact.  Date when the patient left the post-anesthesia care unit (PACU)

columns.name: PatientOutOfPacuInstant
columns.description: This column should no longer be used and will be removed in a future version. Please use the corresponding column in AnesthesiaRecordFact.  Date and time when the patient left the post-anesthesia care unit (PACU)

columns.name: PatientInPhaseIIDateKey
columns.description: This column should no longer be used and will be removed in a future version. Please use the corresponding column in AnesthesiaRecordFact.  Date when the patient arrived in the phase II recovery area

columns.name: PatientInPhaseIIInstant
columns.description: This column should no longer be used and will be removed in a future version. Please use the corresponding column in AnesthesiaRecordFact.  Date and time when the patient arrived in the phase II recovery area

columns.name: PatientOutOfPhaseIIDateKey
columns.description: This column should no longer be used and will be removed in a future version. Please use the corresponding column in AnesthesiaRecordFact.  Date when the patient left the phase II recovery area

columns.name: PatientOutOfPhaseIIInstant
columns.description: This column should no longer be used and will be removed in a future version. Please use the corresponding column in AnesthesiaRecordFact.  Date and time when the patient left the phase II recovery area

columns.name: DeathDateKey
columns.description: This column should no longer be used and will be removed in a future version. Please use the corresponding column in AnesthesiaRecordFact.  The documented date of death of the patient associated with the anesthesia record

columns.name: DeathTimeOfDayKey
columns.description: This column should no longer be used and will be removed in a future version. Please use the corresponding column in AnesthesiaRecordFact.  The documented time of death of the patient associated with the anesthesia record

columns.name: DeathInstant
columns.description: This column should no longer be used and will be removed in a future version. Please use the corresponding column in AnesthesiaRecordFact.  The documented instant of death of the patient associated with the anesthesia record

columns.name: EpiduralToCSectionDateKey
columns.description: This column should no longer be used and will be removed in a future version. Please use the corresponding column in AnesthesiaRecordFact.  The date that the labor epidural transitioned to a C-section

columns.name: EpiduralToCSectionTimeOfDayKey
columns.description: This column should no longer be used and will be removed in a future version. Please use the corresponding column in AnesthesiaRecordFact.  The time of day that the labor epidural transitioned to a C-section

columns.name: EpiduralToCSectionInstant
columns.description: This column should no longer be used and will be removed in a future version. Please use the corresponding column in AnesthesiaRecordFact.  The instant that the labor epidural transitioned to a C-section

columns.name: CaseClassification
columns.description: Case classification for the primary procedure associated with the anesthesia record

columns.name: DischargeCode
columns.description: Hospital discharge code

columns.name: DischargeDisposition
columns.description: Disposition of the patient at discharge

columns.name: RecordType
columns.description: Type of anesthesia record. For Epic data, this will be either case, appointment, or ad hoc.

columns.name: PerioperativeEncounterType
columns.description: Perioperative encounter type. For Epic data, this is the contact type for the encounter (AMB, INP, HOV, OR, or ED).

columns.name: BloodTypeRhFactor
columns.description: Blood type rhesus (Rh) factor

columns.name: MaskDifficultyAssessment
columns.description: Mask difficulty assessment

columns.name: BilledAnesthesiaType
columns.description: Final anesthesia type that was billed. Resolute Professional Billing integration with Epic Anesthesia is required for this metric.

columns.name: BilledAsaScore
columns.description: Final ASA score that was billed. Resolute Professional Billing integration with Epic Anesthesia is required for this metric.

columns.name: BilledProcedureAsaCode
columns.description: Procedure American Society of Anesthesiologists (ASA) code that was billed. Resolute Professional Billing integration with Epic Anesthesia is required for this metric.

columns.name: BilledProcedureCptCode
columns.description: Procedure Current Procedural Terminology (CPT) code that was billed. Resolute Professional Billing integration with Epic Anesthesia is required for this metric.

columns.name: PaymentMethod
columns.description: Primary payment method used by the patient for this anesthesia encounter. Resolute Professional Billing integration with Epic Anesthesia is required for this metric.

columns.name: HighestPreprocedurePainScore
columns.description: Highest pain score recorded during preprocedure

columns.name: FirstPacuPainScore
columns.description: First pain score recorded after the patient moved to the post-anesthesia care unit (PACU)

columns.name: HighestPacuPainScore
columns.description: Highest pain score recorded while the patient was in the post-anesthesia care unit (PACU)

columns.name: HighestCoreTemperatureDuringProcedure
columns.description: Highest core temperature recorded during the procedure

columns.name: HighestTempNearAnesthesiaStop
columns.description: Highest temperature recorded between 30 minutes before and 15 minutes after the end of anesthetic care

columns.name: FirstPostprocedureCoreTemperature
columns.description: First core temperature recorded after the procedure ended

columns.name: AnesthesiaBillingUnits
columns.description: Total number of professional billing units for the anesthesia encounter. This includes base, time, physical status, emergency, age and supplemental units. Resolute Professional Billing integration with Epic Anesthesia is required for this metric.

columns.name: CodingLagDays
columns.description: Number of days between the anesthesia record date of service and when the coder finished coding the encounter (Transaction Post Date) and it is posted to the guarantor account. Resolute Professional Billing integration with Epic Anesthesia is required for this metric.

columns.name: TotalProfessionalCharges
columns.description: Sum of professional charges for the anesthesia record. Resolute Professional Billing integration with Epic Anesthesia is required for this metric.

columns.name: TotalSupplementalCharges
columns.description: Sum of supplemental charges for the anesthesia record. Resolute Professional Billing integration with Epic Anesthesia is required for this metric.

columns.name: AdmissionInstant
columns.description: Date and time that the patient was admitted

columns.name: DischargeInstant
columns.description: This column should no longer be used and will be removed in a future version. Please use the corresponding column in AnesthesiaRecordFact.  Date and time that the patient was discharged

columns.name: NumberOfPonvRiskFactors
columns.description: Number of risk factors for post-operative nausea and vomiting (PONV)

columns.name: NumberOfPovRiskFactors
columns.description: Number of risk factors for post-operative vomiting (POV)

columns.name: NumberOfProphylacticAntiemeticsAdministered
columns.description: Number of prophylactic antiemetics given to the patient preoperatively and intraoperatively

columns.name: NumberOfAntiemeticDosesReceivedInPacu
columns.description: Number of antiemetic doses the patient received while in the post-anesthesia care unit (PACU)

columns.name: HasHistoryOfPonv
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating the patient's history of post-operative nausea or vomiting (PONV). This column returns 1 if the patient has a history of PONV or 0 if they do not.

columns.name: HasHistoryOfDiabetes
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating the patient's history of diabetes. This column returns 1 if the patient has a history of diabetes or 0 if they do not.

columns.name: HasHistoryOfDifficultIntubation
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating the patient's history of difficult intubation. This column returns 1 if the patient has had a difficult intubation or 0 if they have not.

columns.name: HasHistoryOfMotionSickness
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating the patient's history of motion sickness at the time of the anesthesia episode. This column returns 1 if the patient has had motion sickness or 0 if they have not.

columns.name: HasChronicPain
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether the patient has chronic pain at the time of the anesthesia episode. This column returns 1 if the patient has chronic pain or 0 if they do not.

columns.name: HasFamilyHxOfPonv
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating the patient's family history of post-operative nausea or vomiting (PONV) at the time of the anesthesia episode. This column returns 1 if the patient has a family history of PONV or 0 if they do not.

columns.name: HasPsychiatricDisorder
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether the patient had a psychiatric disorder at the time of the anesthesia episode. This column returns 1 if the patient has a psychiatric disorder or 0 if they do not.

columns.name: HadComplications
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether the patient had a complication. This column returns 1 if the patient had a complication or 0 if they did not.

columns.name: MedicationListReviewed
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether the patient's medication list was reviewed. This column returns 1 if the patient's medication list was reviewed or 0 if it was not.

columns.name: MedicationListNotReviewedDueToExclusion
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether there is an exclusion to reviewing the medication list. This rule returns 1 if there is documentation stating the current medication list was not reviewed due to an exclusion or 0 if there is not.

columns.name: HadArterialInjury
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether the patient had an arterial injury. This column returns 1 if the patient had an arterial injury or 0 if they did not.

columns.name: BetaBlockerGivenWithin24Hours
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether the patient received a beta blocker within 24 hours prior to surgery. This column returns 1 if they did or 0 if they did not.

columns.name: BetaBlockerNotGivenWithin24HoursDueToExclusion
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether there was a medical reason for not giving a beta blocker 24 hours prior to incision. This column returns 1 if there was or 0 if there was not.

columns.name: HadStroke
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether the patient had a stroke. This column returns 1 if they did or 0 if they did not.

columns.name: HadCardiacArrest
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether the patient had a cardiac arrest. This column returns 1 if they did or 0 if they did not.

columns.name: HadCardiacBypass
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether the patient had a cardiac bypass. This column returns 1 if they did or 0 if they did not.

columns.name: HadCentralLine
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether the patient had a central line placed. This column returns 1 if they did or 0 if they did not.

columns.name: HandoffChecklistUsed
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether a handoff checklist was used. This column returns 1 if one was used or 0 if one was not.

columns.name: HandoffChecklistNotUsedDueToExclusion
columns.description: 1/0 indicating whether there was a medical exclusion for not using a handoff checklist. This column returns 1 if there was or 0 if there was not.

columns.name: ChecklistUsedPriorToInduction
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether a checklist was used prior to induction. This column returns 1 if one was used or 0 if one was not.

columns.name: HadCornealInjury
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether the patient had a corneal injury. This column returns 1 if they did or 0 if they did not.

columns.name: HadDifficultIntubation
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether the patient had a difficult intubation during this encounter. This column returns 1 if they did or 0 if they did not.

columns.name: HydroxytryptamineAdministered
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether the patient received an administration of 5-Hydroxytryptamine. This column returns 1 if they did or 0 if they did not.

columns.name: AntiemeticSteroidsAdministered
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether the patient received an administration of antiemetic steroids. This column returns 1 if they did or 0 if they did not.

columns.name: PeripheralNerveBlockGiven
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether the patient received a peripheral nerve block. This column returns 1 if they did or 0 if they did not.

columns.name: IsTakingNarcotics
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether the patient was taking narcotics at the time of the anesthesia episode. This column returns 1 if they were or 0 if they were not.

columns.name: HasPreexistingEyeTrauma
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether the patient had a preexisting eye trauma at the time of the anesthesia episode. This column returns 1 if they did or 0 if they did not.

columns.name: InhalationalAnesthesiaGasUsed
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether an inhalational anesthesia gas was used. This column returns 1 if one was used or 0 if one was not.

columns.name: InhalationalAnesthesiaGasUsedForMaintenanceOnly
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether an inhalational anesthesia gas was used for maintenance only. This column returns 1 if a gas was used only for maintenance or 0 if one was not.

columns.name: OpioidAdministration
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether the patient received an opioid administration. This column returns 1 if they did or 0 if they did not.

columns.name: IntentionalHypothermiaInduced
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether hypothermia was intentionally induced. This column returns 1 if it was or 0 if it was not.

columns.name: PharmacologicProphylaxisAntiemeticExclusion
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether there was a medical exclusion for not administering Pharmacologic prophylaxis antiemetics. This column returns 1 if there was or 0 if there was not.

columns.name: AnticholinergicAdministered
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether the patient received an administration of anticholinergics. This column returns 1 if they did or 0 if they did not.

columns.name: AntihistamineAdministered
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether the patient received an administration of antihistamines. This column returns 1 if they did or 0 if they did not.

columns.name: ButyrophenonesAdministered
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether the patient received an administration of butyrophenones. This column returns 1 if they did or 0 if they did not.

columns.name: Nk1ReceptorAntagonistAdministered
columns.description: 1/0 column indicating whether the patient received an administration of NK1 receptor antagonists. This column returns 1 if they did or 0 if they did not.

columns.name: PhenothiazinesAdministered

columns.name: EquivalentMilligramsOfMorphine6HrPostprocedure

For Epic data, this total does not include patient-controlled analgesic (PCA) orders, medications with erroneous calculations, non-opioid medications, feeding product administrations, or the patient's home medications.

AttendingProviderFact.description: The attending provider fact contains information about attending providers. Each row represents an attending provider for a hospital admission or emergency department visit during a given date range.; NOTE: 6/16 TAS:  The criteria require that in Clarity:  1. The encounter on which the provider was the attending is a hospital admission encounter in Epic.  That is, the PAT_ENC_HSP.INP_ADM_DATE is valued.  This implies that attending providers for legacy data (IDX) are not populated, for this column is valued only if the patient was admitted using Epic.    2.  HSP_ATND_PROV.PROV_ID must be valued.  3.  The provider must not have been an attending provider in the ED (HSP_ATND_PROV.ED_ATTEND_YN must be N).

columns.description: Time of day the provider stopped being the attending provider for the patient

columns.name: StartTimeOfDayKeyValue
columns.description: Time of day the provider became the attending provider for the patient; StartTimeOfDayKeyValue is the natural value of StartTimeOfDayKey that you can see without any key decoding

columns.name: HoursAttending
columns.description: Number of hours the provider was the attending provider for the patient. By default, this is calculated as the number of hours between the StartDateKey with the StartTimeOfDayKey and the EndDateKey with the EndTimeOfDayKey columns.

columns.name: EdAttendingProvider
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the provider was an emergency department attending provider. This column returns 1 if the provider was an emergency department attending provider and 0 if the provider wasn't an emergency department attending provider.

columns.name: FirstInEncounter
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the attending provider is the first attending provider for the associated encounter. This column returns 1 if the provider is the first attending and 0 if the provider isn't the first attending. This is calculated by comparing StartDateKey and StartTimeOfDayKey values with other rows for the same encounter.

columns.name: EndTimeOfDayKeyValue
columns.description: Time of day the provider stopped being the attending provider for the patient; EndTimeOfDayKeyValue is the natural value of EndTimeOfDayKey that you can see without any key decoding

columns.name: LastInEdEncounter
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the emergency department attending provider is the last emergency department attending provider for the associated encounter. This column returns 1 if the provider is the last emergency department attending and 0 if the provider isn't the last emergency department attending. This is calculated by comparing EndDateKey and EndTimeOfDayKey values as well as EdAttendingProvider with other rows for the same encounter.

columns.name: FirstInInpatientEncounter
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the attending provider is the first inpatient attending provider for the associated encounter. This column returns 1 if the provider is the first inpatient attending and 0 if the provider isn't the first inpatient attending. This is calculated by comparing StartDateKey and StartTimeOfDayKey values with other rows for the same encounter.

columns.name: LastInEncounter
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the attending provider is the last attending provider for the associated encounter. This column returns 1 if the provider is the last attending and 0 if the provider isn't the last attending. This is calculated by comparing EndDateKey and EndTimeOfDayKey values with other rows for the same encounter.

columns.name: LongestInEncounter
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the attending provider is the longest attending provider for the associated encounter. This column returns 1 if the provider is the longest attending and 0 if the provider isn't the longest attending. This is calculated by comparing StartDateKey and StartTimeOfDayKey with EndDateKey and EndTimeOfDayKey with other rows for the same encounter.

columns.name: LongestInEdEncounter
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the emergency department attending provider is the longest emergency department attending provider for the associated encounter. This column returns 1 if the provider is the longest emergency department attending and 0 if the provider isn't the longest emergency department attending. This is calculated by comparing StartDateKey and StartTimeOfDayKey with EndDateKey and EndTimeOfDayKey as well as EdAttendingProvider with other rows for the same encounter.

columns.name: LongestInInpatientEncounter
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the attending provider is the longest attending provider for the inpatient portion of the associated encounter. This column returns 1 if the provider is the longest attending for the inpatient portion and 0 if the provider isn't the longest attending for the inpatient portion. This is calculated by comparing StartDateKey and StartTimeOfDayKey with EndDateKey and EndTimeOfDayKey as well as EdAttendingProvider with other rows for the same encounter.

BillingProcedureDim.description: The billing procedure dimension contains information about billing procedures. Each row represents a billing procedure for a date range.  This table contains both current and historical information. For current records, IsCurrent has a value of 1. Historical records contain information that is valid for the date range specified by the StartDate and EndDate columns.  For Epic data, this dimension contains only charge, payment, and adjustment procedures.

columns.name: BillingProcedureKey
columns.description: Surrogate key used to uniquely identify the record

columns.name: DeidLds
columns.description: Shows 'DEID' if this is de-identified data and 'LDS' if this is a Limited Data Set

columns.name: DurableKey
columns.description: Durable key used to identify the record

columns.name: BillingProcedureEpicId
columns.description: Epic ID of the billing procedure. This column identifies procedure (EAP) records.

columns.name: Name
columns.description: Name of the billing procedure

columns.name: ShortName
columns.description: Shortened name of the billing procedure

columns.name: PatientFriendlyName

columns.description: Category associated with the billing procedure

columns.description: Billing procedure type

columns.description: Name of the procedure group associated with the billing procedure

columns.description: Indicates whether the billing procedure is a debit or credit procedure

columns.name: CptCode
columns.description: Current Procedural Terminology (CPT) code associated with the billing procedure. This column will be changed in the future to have no change tracking (Type 1).

columns.name: HcpcsCode
columns.description: Healthcare Common Procedure Coding System (HCPCS) code associated with the billing procedure. This column will be changed in the future to have no change tracking (Type 1).

columns.name: AdaCode
columns.description: American Dental Association (ADA) code associated with the billing procedure. This column will be changed in the future to have no change tracking (Type 1).

columns.name: AsaCode
columns.description: American Society of Anesthesiologists (ASA) code associated with the billing procedure. This column will be changed in the future to have no change tracking (Type 1).

columns.name: OtherCodeType
columns.description: Code type associated with the billing procedure for code types other than CPT, HCPCS, ADA, or ASA codes. This column will be changed in the future to have no change tracking (Type 1).

columns.name: OtherCode
columns.description: Code associated with the billing procedure for code types other than CPT, HCPCS, ADA, or ASA codes. This column will be changed in the future to have no change tracking (Type 1).

columns.name: StartDate
columns.description: The date of the execution that loaded a change to at least one column that has snapshot tracking enabled. For the first row loaded for the record this will be an arbitrary date in the past.

columns.name: EndDate
columns.description: The day before the next StartDate for the record. For the IsCurrent = 1 row, this will be an arbitrary date in the future.

columns.name: IsCurrent
columns.description: 1 indicates this is the most recent information, otherwise 0

columns.name: DebitBillingProcedureHcpcsCode
columns.description: Healthcare Common Procedure Coding System (HCPCS) code associated with the billing procedure; DebitBillingProcedureHcpcsCode comes from table BillingProcedureDim, column HcpcsCode by joining on key DebitBillingProcedureKey

columns.name: DebitBillingProcedureOtherCode
columns.description: Code associated with the billing procedure for code types other than CPT, HCPCS, ADA, or ASA codes; DebitBillingProcedureOtherCode comes from table BillingProcedureDim, column OtherCode by joining on key DebitBillingProcedureKey

columns.name: PaymentSource
columns.description: Source of the payment applied to the transaction. For Epic data, this column can contain Cash, Check, Credit Card, EOB, and Voucher.

columns.name: RoutingCode

columns.name: CreditBillingProcedureName

columns.name: AgencyName

columns.name: BillingProcedureCode
columns.description: Billing procedure code associated with the transaction. For Epic data, this column can contain a CPT code, a HCPCS code, or any other type of billing procedure code.

columns.name: CreditBillingProcedureCptCode
columns.description: Current Procedural Terminology (CPT) code associated with the billing procedure; CreditBillingProcedureCptCode comes from table BillingProcedureDim, column CptCode by joining on key CreditBillingProcedureKey

columns.name: BillingProcedureDescription
columns.description: The user-entered procedure description override if specified. For HB transactions, this column will default to the name of the procedure associated with the transaction if no override description is specified. For PB transactions, this column will be blank if no override description is specified.

columns.name: CreditBillingProcedureHcpcsCode
columns.description: Healthcare Common Procedure Coding System (HCPCS) code associated with the billing procedure; CreditBillingProcedureHcpcsCode comes from table BillingProcedureDim, column HcpcsCode by joining on key CreditBillingProcedureKey

columns.name: CreditBillingProcedureOtherCode
columns.description: Code associated with the billing procedure for code types other than CPT, HCPCS, ADA, or ASA codes; CreditBillingProcedureOtherCode comes from table BillingProcedureDim, column OtherCode by joining on key CreditBillingProcedureKey

columns.name: RevenueCode

columns.name: RevenueCodeName
columns.description: Name of the revenue code associated with charge transactions

columns.name: MedicationName

columns.name: MedicationGenericName
columns.description: Generic, non-proprietary name of the medication. For Epic data, if the medication has multiple generic names, this is the first name listed.; MedicationGenericName comes from table MedicationDim, column GenericName by joining on key MedicationKey

columns.name: MedicationTherapeuticClass
columns.description: Therapeutic class that indicates the accepted purpose of the medication; MedicationTherapeuticClass comes from table MedicationDim, column TherapeuticClass by joining on key MedicationKey

columns.name: MedicationPharmaceuticalClass
columns.description: Pharmaceutical class that indicates the chemical family the medication belongs to; MedicationPharmaceuticalClass comes from table MedicationDim, column PharmaceuticalClass by joining on key MedicationKey

columns.name: MedicationPharmaceuticalSubclass
columns.description: Pharmaceutical subclass that indicates the chemical family the medication belongs to. For Epic data, if there are multiple subclasses for the medication, this is the first subclass listed.; MedicationPharmaceuticalSubclass comes from table MedicationDim, column PharmaceuticalSubclass by joining on key MedicationKey

columns.name: MedicationStrength
columns.description: Strength of the medication; MedicationStrength comes from table MedicationDim, column Strength by joining on key MedicationKey

columns.name: MedicationForm
columns.description: Form of the medication; MedicationForm comes from table MedicationDim, column Form by joining on key MedicationKey

columns.name: MedicationRoute
columns.description: Administration route of the medication; MedicationRoute comes from table MedicationDim, column Route by joining on key MedicationKey

columns.name: SupplyName
columns.description: Name of the supply or implant; SupplyName comes from table SurgicalSupplyDim, column Name by joining on key SurgicalSupplyKey

columns.name: SupplyType
columns.description: Type of the supply or implant; SupplyType comes from table SurgicalSupplyDim, column Type by joining on key SurgicalSupplyKey

columns.name: SupplyPrimaryManufacturerCatalogNumber
columns.description: Identification number of the supply or implant in the manufacturer catalog; SupplyPrimaryManufacturerCatalogNumber comes from table SurgicalSupplyDim, column PrimaryManufacturerCatalogNumber by joining on key SurgicalSupplyKey

columns.name: SupplyPrimaryVendor
columns.description: Name of the vendor of the supply or implant; SupplyPrimaryVendor comes from table SurgicalSupplyDim, column PrimaryVendor by joining on key SurgicalSupplyKey

columns.name: SupplyPrimaryVendorCatalogNumber
columns.description: Identification number of the supply or implant in the vendor catalog; SupplyPrimaryVendorCatalogNumber comes from table SurgicalSupplyDim, column PrimaryVendorCatalogNumber by joining on key SurgicalSupplyKey

columns.name: SupplyImplant
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether this item is an implant. This column returns 1 if it is an implant and 0 if it is not an implant. For Epic data, this indicates whether the supply record is currently stored as an implant.; SupplyImplant comes from table SurgicalSupplyDim, column Implant by joining on key SurgicalSupplyKey

columns.name: SupplyOnTheFly
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether this supply was created on the fly. This column returns 1 if the supply was created on the fly and 0 if the supply wasn't created on the fly.; SupplyOnTheFly comes from table SurgicalSupplyDim, column OnTheFly by joining on key SurgicalSupplyKey

columns.name: PrimaryPlanCoverageFinancialClass
columns.description: Financial class of the coverage; PrimaryPlanCoverageFinancialClass comes from table CoverageDim, column CoverageFinancialClass by joining on key PrimaryPlanKey

columns.name: Amount

columns.name: ActiveArTransferAmount

columns.name: ActiveArAdjustmentAmount
columns.description: Adjustment amount against active AR for the transaction. If no value is recorded in the system, this amount is converted to zero.

columns.name: ActiveArPaymentAmount
columns.description: Payment amount against active AR for the transaction. If no value is recorded in the system, this amount is converted to zero.

columns.name: BadDebtTransferAmount

columns.name: BadDebtPaymentAmount

columns.name: ExternalArAdjustmentAmount

columns.name: ExternalArPaymentAmount
columns.description: Payment amount against external AR for the transaction. If no value is recorded in the system, this amount is converted to zero.

columns.name: BalanceTransferAmount
columns.description: Balance transfer amount for the transaction. If no value is recorded in the system, this amount is converted to zero. For Epic data, this column contains the amount being transferred between coverages or liability buckets for the transaction.

columns.name: RvuTotal
columns.description: Total relative value unit (RVU) value for the transaction. If no value is recorded in the system, this amount is converted to zero.

columns.name: RvuWork
columns.description: Work relative value unit (RVU) value for the transaction. If no value is recorded in the system, this amount is converted to zero.

columns.name: RvuOverhead
columns.description: Overhead relative value unit (RVU) value for the transaction. If no value is recorded in the system, this amount is converted to zero.

columns.name: RvuMalpractice
columns.description: Malpractice relative value unit (RVU) value for the transaction. If no value is recorded in the system, this amount is converted to zero.

columns.name: RvuOverride
columns.description: Override value of the relative value unit (RVU) value for the transaction. If no value is recorded in the system, this amount is converted to zero.

columns.name: ExpectedReimbursementAmount
columns.description: Expected reimbursement amount for the transaction. If no value is recorded in the system, this amount is converted to zero. For Epic data, this column is populated only for professional billing transactions.

columns.name: AllowedAmount
columns.description: Allowed amount as reported by the payor for the transaction. If no value is recorded in the system, this amount is converted to zero. For Epic data, this column is populated only for professional billing transactions.

columns.name: OutstandingInsuranceAmount
columns.description: Amount due from insurance on this transaction. If no value is recorded in the system, this amount is converted to zero. For Epic data, this column is populated only for professional billing transactions.

columns.name: OutstandingPatientAmount
columns.description: Amount due from patient on this transaction. If no value is recorded in the system, this amount is converted to zero. For Epic data, this column is populated only for professional billing transactions.

columns.name: OutstandingAmount
columns.description: Amount due on this transaction. If no value is recorded in the system, this amount is converted to zero. For Epic data, this column is populated only for professional billing transactions.

columns.name: UndistributedAmount
columns.description: Undistributed amount on this transaction. If no value is recorded in the system, this amount is converted to zero.

columns.name: OverpostedAmount
columns.description: Overposted credit amount on this transaction. If no value is recorded in the system, this amount is converted to zero. For Epic data, this column is populated only for professional billing transactions.

columns.name: MedicationRepresentativeCost
columns.description: Representative cost of the medication associated with the transaction. If no value is recorded in the system, this amount is converted to zero.

columns.name: MedicationAcquisitionCost
columns.description: Cost of acquiring or purchasing the medication associated with the transaction. If no value is recorded in the system, this amount is converted to zero.

columns.description: Direct variable labor cost associated with the transaction

columns.name: SuppliesCost
columns.description: Supplies cost associated with the transaction

columns.description: General ledger debit account associated with the transaction

columns.name: GeneralLedgerCreditAccount
columns.description: General ledger credit account associated with the transaction

columns.name: InternalControlNumber
columns.description: Internal control number on the payment EOB

columns.name: PaymentReceiptNumber
columns.description: Receipt number for a Payment

columns.name: ReconciliationNumber
columns.description: Reconciliation number associated with the payment transaction

columns.name: ReferenceNumber
columns.description: Reference number (check number) associated with the payment transaction

columns.name: RoutingNumber
columns.description: Routing number associated with the payment transaction

columns.name: OriginalCharge
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the charge is associated with an original charge. This column returns 1 if the transaction is associated with an original charge and 0 if the transaction is not associated with an original charge.

columns.name: HasInsuranceBalanceNoClaim
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the charge has an insurance balance but no associated claim. This column returns 1 if the transaction has an insurance balance but no associated claim, and 0 if the charge has no insurance balance or is associated with a claim. For Epic data, this column will always return 0 for hospital billing transactions.

columns.name: IsRefundAdjustment
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the adjustment transaction was due to a refund. This column returns 1 if the adjustment was due to a refund, and 0 if the adjustment was not due to a refund. For Epic data, this column will always return 0 for professional billing transactions.

columns.name: IsLateCharge
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the charge is considered late. This column returns 1 if the charge is considered late, and 0 if the charge is not considered late. For Epic data, this column will always return 0 for professional billing transactions.

columns.name: IsInactive
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether a transaction is inactive. This column returns 1 if the transaction has been voided, reposted, reversed, or if the transaction is a repost or reversal, and will return 0 otherwise.

columns.name: AccountIsInstitutional
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the account linked to the transaction is designated institutional.  This column returns 1 if the account is designated institutional, and 0 if the account is not designated institutional. For Epic data, this column will always return 0 for professional billing transactions.

columns.name: Count
columns.description: Artificial measure on which calculations can be done. The value is 0 for rows marked as deleted, 1 otherwise.

BirthAnesthesiaBridge.description: The birth anesthesia bridge contains unique combinations of anesthesia methods associated with births. Each row represents an anesthesia method in a combination.

columns.name: BirthAnesthesiaComboKey
columns.description: Combination key used to identify a unique combination of anesthesia methods

columns.name: CategoryKey
columns.description: One of the anesthesia methods in the combination

BirthAttributeValueDim.description: The birth attribute value dimension contains information about values of additional attributes for the birth fact. Each row represents an attribute value for a birth for a date range.   This table contains both current and historical information. For current records, IsCurrent has a value of 1. Historical records contain information that is valid for the date range specified by the StartDate and EndDate columns.   For Epic data, the fact includes SmartData element values with episode contexts unless the data type is Element ID or Image.

columns.name: BirthAttributeValueKey
columns.description: Surrogate key used to uniquely identify the record

columns.name: DurableKey
columns.description: Durable key used to identify the record

columns.name: BirthKey
columns.description: Birth associated with the attribute value

columns.name: AttributeKey
columns.description: Attribute associated with the value. This column will be changed in the future to have no change tracking (Type 1).

columns.name: DateKey
columns.description: Date associated with the attribute value. This column will be changed in the future to have no change tracking (Type 1).

columns.name: StringValue
columns.description: Value of the attribute in string format. This column will be changed in the future to have no change tracking (Type 1).

columns.name: NumericValue
columns.description: Value of the attribute in numeric format. This column will be changed in the future to have no change tracking (Type 1).

columns.name: DateValue
columns.description: Value of the attribute in date format. This column will be changed in the future to have no change tracking (Type 1).

columns.name: StartDate
columns.description: The date of the execution that loaded a change to at least one column that has snapshot tracking enabled. For the first row loaded for the record this will be an arbitrary date in the past.

columns.name: EndDate
columns.description: The day before the next StartDate for the record. For the IsCurrent = 1 row, this will be an arbitrary date in the future.

columns.name: IsCurrent
columns.description: 1 indicates this is the most recent information, otherwise 0

columns.name: _IsInferred
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the record is inferred

columns.name: _IsDeleted
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the record is deleted

columns.name: SpontaneousVaginalDelivery
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the delivery was a spontaneous vaginal delivery. This column returns 1 if the delivery type is spontaneous vaginal, 0 if it is a different delivery type, and NULL if no delivery type was documented.

columns.name: ForcepsDelivery
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the delivery was by forceps. This column returns 1 if the delivery type is forceps, 0 if it is a different delivery type, and NULL if no delivery type was documented.

columns.name: VacuumDelivery
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the delivery was by vacuum. This column returns 1 if the delivery type is vacuum, 0 if it is a different delivery type, and NULL if no delivery type was documented.

columns.name: CesareanDelivery
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the delivery was by cesarean section. This column returns 1 if the delivery type is cesarean, 0 if it is a different delivery type, and NULL if no delivery type was documented.

columns.name: ForcepsAttempted
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether delivery by forceps was attempted. This column returns 1 for positive documentation, 0 for negative documentation, and NULL for no documentation.

columns.name: VacuumAttempted
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether delivery by vacuum was attempted. This column returns 1 for positive documentation, 0 for negative documentation, and NULL for no documentation.

columns.name: LaborAttempted
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether a trial of labor was attempted. This column returns 1 for positive documentation, 0 for negative documentation, and NULL for no documentation.

columns.name: AugmentationUsed
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether augmentation was used. This column returns 1 for positive documentation, 0 for negative documentation, and NULL for no documentation.

columns.name: InductionUsed
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether induction was performed. This column returns 1 for positive documentation, 0 for negative documentation, and NULL for no documentation.

columns.name: EpiduralOrSpinalGiven
columns.description: 1/NULL column that indicates whether epidural or spinal anesthesia was used. This column returns 1 if epidural or spinal anesthesia was documented.

columns.name: SeverePerinealLacerationOccurred
columns.description: 1/NULL column that indicates whether a 3rd or 4th degree perineal laceration occurred. This column returns 1 if a severe perineal laceration was documented.

columns.name: BornAlive
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the newborn was born alive. This column returns 0 if a living status of fetal demise or abortion was documented and 1 otherwise.

columns.name: HiddenAdoptionFlag
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether this delivery involves an adoption where the mother and newborn's information should be hidden from the other's chart. This column returns 1 for positive documentation, 0 for negative documentation, and NULL for no documentation. This column is not populated for historical delivery records documented directly in OB History.

columns.name: BreastMilkGiven
columns.description: 1/NULL column that indicates whether the newborn was given breast milk during their birth encounter. This column returns 1 if breast milk was documented. For Epic data, this column is populated based on "Breast Milk Intake Flowsheets" component configuration.

columns.name: NonBreastMilkGiven
columns.description: 1/NULL column that indicates whether the newborn's diet included anything other than breast milk during the birth encounter. This column returns 1 if the newborn was documented as receiving food that was not breast milk. For Epic data, this column is populated based "Dietary Intake Other Than Breast Milk Flowsheets" component configuration.

columns.name: CesareanExpected
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the delivery was expected to be performed by cesarean section. This column returns 1 if the expected delivery type is cesarean, 0 if it is a different delivery type, and NULL if no delivery type was documented.

columns.name: EssentialDeliveryDocumentationComplete
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether all the essential delivery documentation has been captured for this birth. This column is not populated for historical delivery records.

columns.name: Count
columns.description: Artificial measure on which calculations can be done. The value is 0 for rows marked as deleted, 1 otherwise.

columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the record is inferred

columns.name: HasAcuteCoronarySyndrome
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the coded hospital admission meets the inclusion criteria for this variable. This column stores a 1 if the coded hospital admission has a diagnosis that counts for inclusion in this variable within 12 months prior to or during the admission or 0 otherwise. This variable is defined by CMS as "Acute coronary syndrome (CC 86-87)." CC 86 and 87 are considered complications of care, so they only count for inclusion when they occur prior to the start of this admission.

columns.name: CodedHospitalAdmissionKey
columns.description: Surrogate key used to uniquely identify the record

columns.name: MasterGroupingAdmissionKey
columns.description: The coded hospital admission key for the master grouping admission. The master grouping admission ties together multiple rows that have overlapping admission and discharge dates. If only one of the admissions in the group is derived from billing account (HAR) data, then that is considered the master grouping admission. If multiple admissions derived from billing accounts are grouped together or only claims-derived admissions are grouped together, then the admission with the latest DischargeDateKey is considered the master grouping admission. If multiple admissions have the latest DischargeDateKey, then of those, the admission with the earliest AdmissionDateKey is considered the master grouping admission. If an admission is not in a group, then this column contains the same value as CodedHospitalAdmissionKey.

columns.name: PatientKey
columns.description: Patient associated with the coded hospital admission

columns.name: EncounterKey
columns.description: Encounter associated with the coded hospital admission

columns.name: AgeAtAdmissionKey
columns.description: Patient age as of the coded hospital admission date. Calculated based on the AdmissionDateKey and the BirthDate column in PatientDim.

columns.name: AgeAtDischargeKey
columns.description: Patient age as of the coded hospital discharge date. Calculated based on the DischargeDateKey and the BirthDate column in PatientDim.

columns.name: AdmissionDateKey
columns.description: Date the patient started receiving care at the hospital

columns.name: AdmissionTimeOfDayKey
columns.description: Time of day the patient started receiving care at the hospital. If only date information was available for this coded hospital admission, then this column will store a 0.

columns.name: InpatientAdmissionDateKey
columns.description: Date the patient started receiving inpatient acute care

columns.name: InpatientAdmissionTimeOfDayKey
columns.description: Time of day the patient started receiving inpatient acute care. If only date information was available for this coded hospital admission, then this column will store a 0.

columns.name: DischargeDateKey
columns.description: Date the patient was discharged

columns.name: DischargeTimeOfDayKey
columns.description: Time of day the patient was discharged. If only date information was available for this coded hospital admission, then this column will store a 0.

columns.name: PlaceOfServiceKey
columns.description: Place of service associated with the coded hospital admission

columns.name: DischargeDepartmentKey
columns.description: The department from which the patient was discharged

columns.name: AttendingProviderKey
columns.description: Provider who managed the overall care of the admitted patient

columns.name: AttendingProviderDurableKey
columns.description: Provider who managed the overall care of the admitted patient

columns.name: DischargingProviderDurableKey
columns.description: The provider who discharged the patient

columns.name: OperatingProviderKey
columns.description: Provider who had the primary responsibility for performing the surgical procedure

columns.name: OperatingProviderDurableKey
columns.description: Provider who had the primary responsibility for performing the surgical procedure

columns.name: PrimaryDiagnosisKey
columns.description: Primary diagnosis for the patient for the coded hospital admission

columns.name: PrimaryProcedureKey
columns.description: Primary procedure for the patient for the coded hospital admission

columns.name: PrimaryProcedureDurableKey
columns.description: Primary procedure for the patient for the coded hospital admission

columns.name: BillingDrgKey
columns.description: Diagnosis Related Group (DRG) that was billed for this coded admission

columns.name: PrimaryCoverageKey
columns.description: Primary coverage associated with the coded hospital admission. This is the earliest coverage in the coverage list that is not marked to be ignored as primary payer and therefore this coverage is used to determine the account financial class.

columns.name: Overall30DayIndexAdmissionKey
columns.description: For readmissions, the corresponding index coded hospital admission. The Billing Index Metric Load package of CodedHospitalAdmissionReadmissionDataMart must be enabled for this column to populate. The HospitalWidePriorAdmissionKey column in CodedHospitalAdmissionReadmissionDataMart contains the result of the same readmission metric.

columns.name: Overall30DayReadmissionKey
columns.description: For index admissions, the coded hospital admission which qualifies as a readmission to the index admission. The Billing Index Metric Load package of CodedHospitalAdmissionReadmissionDataMart must be enabled for this column to populate. The HospitalWideNextAdmissionKey column in CodedHospitalAdmissionReadmissionDataMart contains the result of the same readmission metric.

columns.name: PrecedingEdEncounterKey
columns.description: ED visit that preceded this admission, if any. For claims derived admissions, this will be populated with claims derived ED visits starting on the same day or previous day as the claims derived admission. For HAR based admissions, this will be populated with the encounter associated with the primary CSN of the HAR.

columns.name: AdmissionServiceType
columns.description: Type of service provided for the coded hospital admission. For Epic data, this can be Short-term Acute Care, Long-term Acute Care, Inpatient Psychiatric, or Inpatient Rehabilitation.

columns.name: BillingDrgCode
columns.description: Billing Diagnosis Related Group (DRG) code

columns.name: BillingDrgType
columns.description: Billing Diagnosis Related Group (DRG) type

columns.name: BillingInpatientLengthOfStayInDays
columns.description: The total number of days between admission and discharge calculated as the difference between the discharge time and admission time rounded to the nearest number of days. If this would round to 0, it is treated as a length of stay of 1 day.

columns.name: HospitalAccountEpicId
columns.description: Epic ID of the hospital account associated with the coded hospital admission. This column identifies account (HAR) records.

columns.name: AdmissionTypeCode
columns.description: Recognized code for the type and priority of services associated with the coded hospital admission

columns.name: AdmissionType
columns.description: Type and priority of service associated with the coded hospital admission

columns.name: AdmissionSourceCode
columns.description: Recognized code for the source of the referral for the admission associated with the coded hospital admission

columns.name: AdmissionSource
columns.description: Source of the referral for the coded hospital admission

columns.name: DischargeDispositionCode
columns.description: Recognized code for the discharge disposition of the patient associated with the coded hospital admission

columns.name: DischargeDisposition
columns.description: Patient discharge disposition

columns.name: AdmissionInstant
columns.description: Date and time the patient started receiving care at the hospital

columns.name: InpatientAdmissionInstant
columns.description: Date and time the patient started receiving inpatient acute care

columns.name: DischargeInstant
columns.description: Date and time the patient was discharged

columns.name: TotalDurationOfEncounterInDays
columns.description: Number of days associated with the coded hospital admission. By default, this is calculated as the number of days between the AdmissionDateKey and the DischargeDateKey. Admissions where admission and discharge occur on the same day are considered to have a total duration of 1 day.

columns.name: PatientTaskCompletionRateSinceLastDischarge
columns.description: The completion percentage for all patient assigned tasks that have been active since the last discharge.

columns.name: DaysSincePriorAdmission
columns.description: Number of days between the admission date of the coded hospital admission and the discharge date of the patient's prior coded hospital admission. This column will not be populated for patients that have no prior coded hospital admission or for non-master coded hospital admissions.

columns.name: DaysUntilNextAdmission
columns.description: Number of days between the discharge date of the coded hospital admission and the admission date of the patient's subsequent coded hospital admission. This column will not be populated for patients that have no subsequent coded hospital admission or for non-master coded hospital admissions.

columns.name: Overall30DayReadmissionRateInDenominator
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates if this admission is an index admission with or without any subsequent readmissions based on an overall 30-day readmission definition. An index admission is any admission except those for which the patient was discharged against medical advice, was declared deceased, was transferred to another acute care facility, or was admitted with a primary diagnosis relating to psychiatric, rehabilitation, or cancer treatments. Non-master coded hospital admissions are excluded from qualifying as index admissions or readmissions. This column returns 1 if the admission is considered an index admission and 0 if it is not. The Billing Index Metric Load package of CodedHospitalAdmissionReadmissionDataMart must be enabled for this column to populate. The HospitalWideAllAgeInDenominator column in CodedHospitalAdmissionReadmissionDataMart contains the result of the same readmission metric.

columns.name: Overall30DayReadmissionRateInNumerator
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates if this admission is an index admission with a subsequent readmission based on an overall 30-day readmission definition. An index admission has a readmission if the next subsequent admission for that patient within 30 days does not have an always-planned procedure, an always-planned diagnosis, or a combination of a potentially-planned procedure and an acute principal discharge diagnosis. Non-master coded hospital admissions do not qualify as index admissions or readmissions. This column returns 1 if the admission is an index admission with a readmission and 0 if it is not. The Billing Index Metric Load package of CodedHospitalAdmissionReadmissionDataMart must be enabled for this column to populate. The HospitalWideAllAgeInNumerator column in CodedHospitalAdmissionReadmissionDataMart contains the result of the same readmission metric.

columns.name: HasEncounterDerivedAdmissionServiceType
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the encounter that makes up this admission contains a derived service type from EncounterFact. This column returns 1 if the admission contains a derived service type and 0 if it does not.

columns.name: IsMaster
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the encounter that makes up this admission is a master grouping admission. This column returns 1 if the encounter is a master grouping admission and 0 if it is not.

columns.name: IsPotentiallyPreventable
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether this admission is considered potentially preventable. This column returns 1 if the admission is potentially preventable and 0 if it is not.

columns.name: Count
columns.description: Artificial measure on which calculations can be done. The value is 0 for rows marked as deleted, 1 otherwise.

columns.name: _IsInferred
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the record is inferred

columns.name: _IsDeleted
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the record is deleted

columns.name: _HasSourceClaimBasedEvents
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the record is influenced by the ClaimBasedEvents source

columns.name: _DeletedFromSourceClaimBasedEvents
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the record is deleted from the ClaimBasedEvents source

columns.name: FirstCoverageKey
columns.description: First coverage associated with the coded hospital admission. In cases where coverages are marked to be ignored for primary payer, this column will be the first coverage in the filing order even if it is marked as ignored.

CodedProcedureFact.description: The coded procedure fact contains information about procedures coded to a hospital account. Each row represents a procedure.   For Epic data, the fact includes the primary code set used to code the account, the alternate code set, coded CPTs, and CPTs from the combined service line.

columns.name: CodedProcedureKey
columns.description: Surrogate key used to uniquely identify the record

columns.name: DeidLds
columns.description: Shows 'DEID' if this is de-identified data and 'LDS' if this is a Limited Data Set

columns.name: PatientDurableKey
columns.description: This is the de-identified version of PatientDim.DurableKey.  There is one value per person. Use this to join to the same patient in other tables, or to re-identify the patient at a later date with IRB approval

columns.name: BillingAccountKey
columns.description: Billing account associated with the coded procedure

columns.name: ProcedureTerminologyKey

columns.name: EncounterKey
columns.description: This is the de-identified version of EncounterFact.EncounterKey.  Each value is unique to the encounter across all patients. Use this to join to the same encounter in other tables, or to re-identify the encounter at a later date with IRB approval

columns.name: PerformingProviderKey

columns.name: PerformingProviderDurableKey
columns.description: Performing provider associated with the coded procedure

columns.name: AnesthesiaProviderKey

columns.name: ProcedureTerminologyName

columns.name: AnesthesiaProviderDurableKey

columns.name: ProcedureTerminologyCodeSet

columns.name: ProcedureDateKey

columns.name: SourceName

columns.name: PerformingProviderType

columns.name: AnesthesiaType
