DateDim.description: The date dimension contains information about dates. Each row represents a date.  The dimension supports dates from January 1, 0001 to December 30, 9999.

columns.name: DateKey
columns.description: Surrogate key used to uniquely identify the record. The value is the combination of the four-digit year from 0001 to 9999, the two-digit month from 01 to 12, and the two-digit day from 01 to 31.

columns.name: DeidLds
columns.description: Shows 'DEID' if this is de-identified data and 'LDS' if this is a Limited Data Set

columns.name: DateValue
columns.description: Value in date format

columns.name: DisplayString
columns.description: Display string for the date formatted by the configuration settings

columns.name: DayOfWeek
columns.description: Name of the day of the week

columns.name: WeekNumber
columns.description: Number of the week since the beginning of the year for the date from 1 to 54

columns.name: LastFridayDate
columns.description: Date of the Friday prior to the date. If the date is a Friday, this column holds that date value. This column will be NULL for dates earlier than January 5, 1753.

columns.name: MonthEndDate
columns.description: Date of the last day of the month for the date. This column will be NULL for dates earlier than January 1, 1753.

columns.name: DayOfMonth
columns.description: Number of the day of the month for the date from 1 to 31

columns.name: MonthName
columns.description: Name of the month for the date

columns.name: MonthNumber
columns.description: Number of the month of the year for the date from 1 to 12

columns.name: QuarterNumber
columns.description: Number of the quarter for the date from 1 to 4

columns.name: DayOfYear
columns.description: Number of the day of the year for the date from 1 to 366

columns.name: EpicDte
columns.description: Number of days since December 31, 1840 for the date. This column will be NULL for dates earlier than December 31, 1840 and dates later than September 27, 2173.

columns.name: EpicDat
columns.description: Epic contact date sequence number for the date. The value is 121,531 minus the number of days since December 31, 1840. This column will be NULL for dates earlier than December 31, 1840 and dates later than September 27, 2173.

columns.name: EpicInstantAtMidnight
columns.description: The point in time for midnight of the date.  The value is the number of seconds since midnight on December 31, 1840. This column will be NULL for dates earlier than December 31, 1840.

columns.name: Year
columns.description: Year for the date from 0001 to 9999

columns.name: OccurrenceInMonth
columns.description: Number of times the day of the week has occurred in the month for the date from 1 to 5

columns.name: TomorrowDate
columns.description: The day following the date

columns.name: YearMonth
columns.description: String containing the concatenation of the four-digit year and the two-digit month

columns.name: FiscalYear
columns.description: Fiscal year for the date from 1753 to 9999. This column will be NULL for fiscal dates that are earlier than January 1, 1753 or later than December 31, 9999.

columns.name: FiscalMonth
columns.description: Fiscal month of the year for the date from 1 to 12. This column will be NULL for fiscal dates that are earlier than January 1, 1753 or later than December 31, 9999.

columns.name: FiscalQuarter
columns.description: Fiscal quarter of the year for the date from 1 to 4. This column will be NULL for fiscal dates that are earlier than January 1, 1753 or later than December 31, 9999.

columns.name: Weekend
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the date is on a weekend. This column returns 1 if the date is on a weekend and 0 if the date is on a weekday.

columns.name: IndexDayOfWeek
columns.description: Number of the day of the week for the date from 1 to 7. The first day of the week is set in the configuration settings

columns.name: DayOfWeekAbbreviation
columns.description: Abbreviated name of the day of the week

columns.name: FormattedMonthYear
columns.description: String containing the concatenation of the month name, a space, and the four-digit year

columns.name: FormattedQuarterNumber
columns.description: String containing the concatenation of "Q" and the number of the quarter for the date

columns.name: FormattedQuarterYear
columns.description: String containing the concatenation of the two-digit quarter (Q + quarter number), a space, and the four-digit year

columns.name: IsDayAfterHoliday
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the date is the day after a recognized holiday. This column returns 1 if the date is the day after a holiday and 0 if the date isn't a day after a holiday.

columns.name: IsDayBeforeHoliday
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the date is the day before a recognized holiday. This column returns 1 if the date is the day before a holiday and 0 if the date isn't a day before a holiday.

columns.name: IsHoliday
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the date is a recognized holiday. This column returns 1 if the date is a holiday and 0 if the date isn't a holiday. This column is based entirely on DATE_DIMENSION.HOLIDAY_YN in Clarity.

columns.name: IsoWeekNumber
columns.description: Number of the week since the beginning of the year for the date as defined by the International Organization for Standardization (ISO)

columns.name: IsoWeekYear
columns.description: String containing the concatenation of the two-digit week number, a space, and the four-digit year as defined by the International Organization for Standardization (ISO)

columns.name: IsoYearWeek
columns.description: String containing the concatenation of the four-digit year, a space, and the two-digit week number as defined by the International Organization for Standardization (ISO)

columns.name: IsWeekendIncludingFriday
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the date is on a weekend. This column returns 1 if the date is on a weekend and 0 if the date is on a weekday. Here, weekend is defined as Friday, Saturday, and Sunday.

columns.name: MonthNameAbbreviation
columns.description: Abbreviated name of the month for the date

columns.name: MonthStartDate
columns.description: Date of the first day of the month for the date. This column will be NULL for dates earlier than January 1, 1753.

columns.name: MonthYear
columns.description: String containing the concatenation of the two-digit month, a space, and the four-digit year

columns.name: NextYearDate
columns.description: Date one year after the date

columns.name: PreviousYearDate
columns.description: Date one year prior to the date. This column will be NULL for dates earlier than January 1, 1754.

columns.name: QuarterEndDate
columns.description: Date of the last day of the quarter for the date. This column will be NULL for dates earlier than January 1, 1753.

columns.name: QuarterStartDate
columns.description: Date of the first day of the quarter for the date. This column will be NULL for dates earlier than January 1, 1753.

columns.name: QuarterYear
columns.description: String containing the concatenation of the one-digit quarter, a space, and the four-digit year

columns.name: WeekEndDate
columns.description: Date of the last day of the week for the date. This column will be NULL for dates earlier than January 1, 1753.

columns.name: WeekStartDate
columns.description: Date of the first day of the week for the date. This column will be NULL for dates earlier than January 1, 1753.

columns.name: WeekYear
columns.description: String containing the concatenation of the two-digit week number, a space, and the four-digit year

columns.name: YearEndDate
columns.description: Date of the last day of the year for the date. This column will be NULL for dates earlier than January 1, 1753.

columns.name: YearFormattedMonth
columns.description: String containing the concatenation of the four-digit year, a space, and the month name

columns.name: YearFormattedQuarter
columns.description: String containing the concatenation of the four-digit year, a space, and the two-digit quarter (Q + quarter number)

columns.name: YearQuarter
columns.description: String containing the concatenation of the four-digit year, a space, and the one-digit quarter

columns.name: YearStartDate
columns.description: Date of the first day of the year for the date. This column will be NULL for dates earlier than January 1, 1753.

columns.name: YearWeek
columns.description: String containing the concatenation of the four-digit year, a space, and the two-digit week number

DepartmentDim.description: The department dimension contains information about locations in a facility. For Epic data, data is imported at each level of granularity, with records at each level of granularity containing information about the levels above it.

columns.name: RoomEpicId

columns.name: RoomName

DiagnosisBridge.description: The diagnosis bridge contains unique combinations of diagnoses associated with other records. Each row represents a diagnosis in a combination.  For Epic data, hospital-acquired diagnoses are those on the problem list that are not deleted and have a present on admission value of No. Patient problem list diagnoses are those on the problem list that are active. Present on admission diagnoses are those on the problem list that are not deleted and have a present on admission value of Yes. Professional billing account-associated diagnoses are extracted for single billing office service areas based on the associated single billing office hospital account.

DiagnosisEventFact.description: The diagnosis event fact contains information about diagnoses attributed to patients. Each row represents an event attributing a diagnosis to a patient.   For Epic data, the fact includes diagnosis information from the following places: encounter diagnoses, problem lists, medical histories, professional charge transaction diagnoses, final coded diagnoses, and external injury codes. It might include Health Maintenance modifiers that your organization maps to diagnoses.   Professional charge diagnoses are included unless the transaction is voided.   Final diagnoses and external injury codes are included when all of the following requirements are met: the coding is complete, the final diagnoses and external injury codes haven't been marked for exclusion from clinical reporting, and the hospital account hasn't been voided.

EncounterFact.description: The encounter fact contains information about encounters documented in an EMR and encounters derived from billing data. Each row represents an encounter. Encounters from an EMR are flagged with IsDerivedFromBilling = 0 and encounters derived from billing data are flagged with IsDerivedFromBilling = 1. For Epic EMR data, one encounter is one CSN. For encounters derived from billing data, Epic has released definitions that combine multiple outgoing and paid claims into one encounter based on comparing attributes like patient, provider, and date.; NOTE: 6/5 TAS: EncounterFact matches CLARITY.dbo.PAT_ENC by row count.  Enumerating all Contact Types (EPT/30) in PAT_ENC.ENC_TYPE_C will match the analogous result of enumerating Types from EncounterFact.EncounterProfileKey, which links to EncounterProfileDim.

HospitalAdmissionAttributeValueDim.description: The hospital admission attribute value dimension contains information about values of additional attributes for the hospital admission fact. Each row represents an attribute value for a hospital admission encounter for a date range.   This table contains both current and historical information. For current records, IsCurrent has a value of 1. Historical records contain information that is valid for the date range specified by the StartDate and EndDate columns.   For Epic data, the fact includes SmartData element values with encounter contexts unless the data type is Element ID or Image.

HospitalAdmissionFact.description: The hospital admission fact contains information about hospital admissions. Each row represents a hospital admission encounter. For Epic data, the fact includes records with an inpatient or observation patient class where the encounter was not canceled. Encounters are included if the patient had an inpatient patient class for any part of the admission or ended the admission with a final patient class of observation. Data for other Epic encounters can be found in EncounterFact.; NOTE: 12/8 TAS: IDX Admits were imported.  6/17 TAS: Represents only the number of rows in PAT_ENC_HSP where the INP_ADM_DATE is  valued.  These represent hospital admissions which were created in APeX; admits created in IDX are not currently in this fact.

ImagingFact.description: The imaging fact contains information about imaging studies. Each row represents an imaging study.

columns.name: ImagingKey
columns.description: Surrogate key used to uniquely identify the record

columns.name: DeidLds
columns.description: Shows 'DEID' if this is de-identified data and 'LDS' if this is a Limited Data Set

columns.name: PatientKey
columns.description: Patient associated with the imaging study

columns.name: PatientDurableKey
columns.description: This is the de-identified version of PatientDim.DurableKey.  There is one value per person. Use this to join to the same patient in other tables, or to re-identify the patient at a later date with IRB approval

columns.name: EncounterKey
columns.description: This is the de-identified version of EncounterFact.EncounterKey.  Each value is unique to the encounter across all patients. Use this to join to the same encounter in other tables, or to re-identify the encounter at a later date with IRB approval

columns.name: PerformedProcedureStepStartDateKey
columns.description: Date when the Digital Imaging and Communications in Medicine (DICOM) Performed Procedure Step (PPS) for the study started. For Epic data, if a modality sends multiple PPS start times, this will be the minimum.

columns.name: PerformedProcedureStepEndDateKey
columns.description: Date when the Digital Imaging and Communications in Medicine (DICOM) Performed Procedure Step (PPS) for the study ended. For Epic data, if a modality sends multiple PPS end times, this will be the maximum.

columns.description: Date when the appointment or case for the order was scheduled. For Epic data, this is the date the appointment was made (for non-invasive exams) or the date the case was added to the schedule (for invasive procedures). In the event an appointment or case is rescheduled or changed, this column contains the original date it was scheduled.

columns.name: PerformedProcedureStepStartInstant

columns.name: PerformedProcedureStepEndInstant
columns.description: Date and time when the Digital Imaging and Communications in Medicine (DICOM) Performed Procedure Step (PPS) ended. For Epic data, if a modality sends multiple PPS end times, this will be the maximum.

columns.name: CancelingInstant
columns.description: Date and time when the study was canceled

columns.name: CheckInInstant
columns.description: Date and time when the patient was checked in. For Epic data, if the check-in action is performed multiple times, this will be the first check-in time that was not canceled.

columns.name: ScheduledOnInstant
columns.description: Date and time when the appointment or case was scheduled. For Epic data, this is the date and time the appointment was made (for non-invasive exams) or the date and time the case was added to the schedule (for invasive procedures). In the event an appointment or case is rescheduled or changed, this column contains the original date and time it was scheduled.

columns.name: ProtocolledInstant

columns.name: NumberOfRepeatsForFirstRepeatReason

columns.name: NumberOfRepeatsForSecondRepeatReason

columns.name: NumberOfRepeatsForThirdRepeatReason
columns.description: Number of repeats for the third repeat reason. For Epic data, this is the number of repeats for the repeat reason with the third largest number of repeats.

columns.name: Canceled
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the study is canceled. This column returns 1 if the study was canceled and 0 if it was not canceled

columns.name: WetRead
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether a wet read was performed on the order. This column returns 1 if a wet read was performed and 0 if a wet read was not performed.

columns.name: IsAbnormal
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the study contains abnormal results. This column returns 1 if there are abnormal results and 0 if there are not abnormal results.

columns.name: Count
columns.description: Artificial measure on which calculations can be done. The value is 0 for rows marked as deleted, 1 otherwise.

LabDim.description: The lab dimension contains information about labs, sections, and case types. Each row represents a lab, section, or case type for a date range.  For Epic data, data is imported at each level of granularity, with records at each level of granularity containing information about the levels above it.  This table contains both current and historical information. For current records, IsCurrent has a value of 1. Historical records contain information that is valid for the date range specified by the StartDate and EndDate columns.

columns.name: LabKey
columns.description: Surrogate key used to uniquely identify the record

columns.name: DeidLds
columns.description: Shows 'DEID' if this is de-identified data and 'LDS' if this is a Limited Data Set

columns.name: DurableKey
columns.description: Durable key used to identify the record

columns.name: LabName
columns.description: Name of the lab. This column will be changed in the future to have no change tracking (Type 1).

columns.name: LabAddress
columns.description: Street address for the lab. Only the first 300 characters are stored. This column will be changed in the future to have no change tracking (Type 1).

columns.name: LabCity
columns.description: City for the address associated with the lab. This column will be changed in the future to have no change tracking (Type 1).

columns.name: LabCounty
columns.description: County for the address associated with the lab. This column will be changed in the future to have no change tracking (Type 1).

columns.name: LabStateOrProvince
columns.description: State or province for the address associated with the lab. This column will be changed in the future to have no change tracking (Type 1).

columns.name: LabCountry
columns.description: Country for the address associated with the lab. This column will be changed in the future to have no change tracking (Type 1).

columns.name: LabPostalCode
columns.description: Postal code for the address associated with the lab. This column will be changed in the future to have no change tracking (Type 1).

columns.name: StartDate
columns.description: The date of the execution that loaded a change to at least one column that has snapshot tracking enabled. For the first row loaded for the record this will be an arbitrary date in the past.

columns.name: EndDate
columns.description: The day before the next StartDate for the record. For the IsCurrent = 1 row, this will be an arbitrary date in the future.

columns.name: IsCurrent
columns.description: 1 indicates this is the most recent information, otherwise 0

columns.name: LabEpicId
columns.description: Epic ID of the laboratory. This column identifies lab definition (LDF) records of type 6-Laboratory.

columns.description: Source of the testing request. For Epic data, this column can contain Inpatient, Outpatient, or Requisition.

columns.name: VerificationStatus

columns.name: LastCorrectionReason
columns.description: Reason for the most recent authorized result correction or amendment

columns.name: RequiredData
columns.description: Indicates whether the test's results are missing required or recommended data

columns.name: IsHighPriority
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the test was ordered as a high priority. This column returns 1 if the test is high priority and 0 if the test isn't high priority.

columns.name: IsTimedPriority
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the test was ordered as a timed priority. This column returns 1 if the test is timed priority and 0 if the test isn't timed priority.

columns.name: IsAbnormal
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the test's results are considered abnormal. This column returns 1 if the test's results are abnormal and 0 if they are not abnormal.

columns.name: IsCritical
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the test's results are considered critical. This column returns 1 if the test's results are critical and 0 if they are not critical.

columns.name: IsCorrection
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the test's results have had at least one correction or amendment authorized. This column returns 1 if the test's results have had at least one correction or amendment authorized and 0 if there has been no correction or amendment.

columns.name: IsAddendum
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the test's results have had at least one addendum added. This column returns 1 if the test's results have had at least one addendum authorized and 0 if there has been no addendum.

columns.name: IsQualityControl
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether this is a quality control. This column returns 1 if the test is a quality control and 0 if it is not a quality control.

columns.name: IsFrozenSpecimen
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether this test is on a frozen specimen. This column returns 1 if the test is on a frozen specimen and 0 if it is not on a frozen specimen.

columns.name: IsAddOn
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether this test is an add-on. This column returns 1 if the test is an add-on and 0 if it is not an add-on.

columns.name: IsAutoVerified
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the test's results have ever been auto-verified. This column returns 1 if any portion of the test has been auto-verified at least one time and 0 if there has been no auto-verification. This column may be null if the verification process is unknown.

columns.name: IsDelta
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether any component on the test was flagged as a delta. This column returns 1 if any component has a delta flag and 0 otherwise.

columns.name: IsInstrumentError
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether any component or isolate on the test logged an instrument error. This column returns 1 if any component or isolate has at least one instrument error flag and 0 if there are no instrument error flags. This column may be null if instrument information is unknown.

columns.name: IsReportable
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the test's results are considered reportable. This column returns 1 if the test's results are reportable and 0 otherwise.

columns.name: Count
columns.description: Artificial measure on which calculations can be done. The value is 0 for rows marked as deleted, 1 otherwise.

LoincDim.description: The Logical Observation Identifiers Names and Codes (LOINC®) dimension contains information about LOINC codes. Each row represents a LOINC code.

MedicationAdministrationFact.description: The medication administration fact contains information about medication and feeding product administrations. Each row represents a medication or feeding product administration.  For Epic data, the fact table includes records with administration actions: given, new bag, bolus, and push. It also includes custom actions mapped to those actions.

By default, this is calculated as the number of minutes between the ScheduledAdministrationDateKey with the ScheduledAdministrationTimeOfDayKey and the AdministrationDateKey with the AdministrationTimeOfDayKey columns. If the administration was before the scheduled time, this column returns NULL.

By default, this is calculated as the number of minutes between the ScheduledAdministrationDateKey with the ScheduledAdministrationTimeOfDayKey and the AdministrationDateKey with the AdministrationTimeOfDayKey columns. columns.name: FillPharmacyType

columns.name: Mode
columns.description: Mode for the dispense. For Epic data, this column can contain Inpatient or Outpatient.

columns.name: FillPharmacyPhysicalType
columns.description: Physical type of the pharmacy. For Epic data, this column can contain Standard, Automated Dispensing Station, Robotic Dispensing System, Automated Prescription Filling System, or other values.; FillPharmacyPhysicalType comes from table PharmacyDim, column PhysicalType by joining on key FillPharmacyKey

columns.name: FillPharmacyFacilityAdministeredMedicationsSupported
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the pharmacy supports facility administered medications. This column returns 1 if the pharmacy supports facility administered medications and 0 if the pharmacy doesn't support facility administered medications.; FillPharmacyFacilityAdministeredMedicationsSupported comes from table PharmacyDim, column FacilityAdministeredMedicationsSupported by joining on key FillPharmacyKey

columns.name: DispenseCode
columns.description: Code for the dispense. For Epic data, this column isn't populated for outpatient dispenses.

columns.name: DeliveryMethod
columns.description: Delivery method for the dispense

columns.name: FillPharmacyPrescriptionsSupported
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the pharmacy supports prescriptions. This column returns 1 if the pharmacy supports prescriptions and 0 if the pharmacy doesn't support prescriptions.; FillPharmacyPrescriptionsSupported comes from table PharmacyDim, column PrescriptionsSupported by joining on key FillPharmacyKey

columns.name: DispenseType
columns.description: The type of dispense. For Epic data, this column is not applicable for outpatient orders. This column can contain Non-Clinical ADS Override, ADS Override, ADS Dispense, Cart, First Dose, Bulk Charge, or Redispense.

columns.name: RedispenseReason
columns.description: The reason the dispense user documented why the medication was redispensed. For Epic data, if the dispense is not a redispense or is outpatient, this column is not applicable.

columns.name: ReleaseDateKeyValue
columns.description: Date the associated order was released; ReleaseDateKeyValue is the natural value of ReleaseDateKey that you can see without any key decoding

columns.name: ReleaseTimeOfDayKeyValue
columns.description: Time of day the associated order was released; ReleaseTimeOfDayKeyValue is the natural value of ReleaseTimeOfDayKey that you can see without any key decoding

columns.name: VerifiedDateKeyValue
columns.description: Date the dispense was verified. For Epic data, this is the date the dispense was first verified.; VerifiedDateKeyValue is the natural value of VerifiedDateKey that you can see without any key decoding

columns.name: MedicationOrderEpicId
columns.description: Epic ID of the medication order. This column identifies order (ORD) records.

columns.name: ReleaseInstant
columns.description: Date and time the associated order was released. For outpatient dispenses in Epic, this is the date and time that the fill reached the pending fill status.

columns.name: VerifiedTimeOfDayKeyValue
columns.description: Time of day the dispense was verified. For Epic data, this is the time of day the dispense was first verified.; VerifiedTimeOfDayKeyValue is the natural value of VerifiedTimeOfDayKey that you can see without any key decoding

columns.name: VerifiedInstant
columns.description: Date and time the dispense was verified. For Epic data, this is the date the dispense was first verified.

columns.name: ReadyToPackageInstant
columns.description: Date and time the dispense was ready to be packaged. For Epic data, this column isn't populated for inpatient dispenses.

columns.name: ReadyToDispenseDateKeyValue
columns.description: Date the dispense was ready to be dispensed. For Epic data, this is when the labels were printed.; ReadyToDispenseDateKeyValue is the natural value of ReadyToDispenseDateKey that you can see without any key decoding

columns.name: ReadyToDispenseInstant
columns.description: Date and time the dispense was ready to be dispensed. For Epic data, this is the date and time when labels were printed for inpatient dispenses.  For inpatient dispenses currently in the dispense queue, this is the date and time that the dispense was added to the queue. For outpatient dispenses in Epic, this is the date and time the fill was ready to be given to the patient.

columns.name: ReadyToDispenseTimeOfDayKeyValue
columns.description: Time of day the dispense was ready to be dispensed. For Epic data, this is when the labels were printed.; ReadyToDispenseTimeOfDayKeyValue is the natural value of ReadyToDispenseTimeOfDayKey that you can see without any key decoding

columns.name: DispensePreparedInstant
columns.description: Date and time the dispense was prepared. For outpatient dispenses in Epic, this is the date and time that the fill was dispensed.

columns.name: FinalDispenseCheckInstant
columns.description: Date and time the dispense was checked and approved or rejected before it was sent to the patient. For Epic inpatient data, if the dispense was checked twice, this is the date and time of the second check. This column isn't populated for outpatient dispenses.

columns.name: DispensePreparedDateKeyValue
columns.description: Date the dispense was prepared; DispensePreparedDateKeyValue is the natural value of DispensePreparedDateKey that you can see without any key decoding

columns.name: DispenseSentInstant
columns.description: Date and time the dispense was sent. For outpatient dispenses in Epic, this is the date and time that the fill was shipped.

columns.name: DispenseReceivedInstant
columns.description: Date and time the dispense was received. For outpatient dispenses in Epic, this is the date and time that the fill was sent out for delivery.

columns.name: DispensePreparedTimeOfDayKeyValue
columns.description: Time of day the dispense was prepared; DispensePreparedTimeOfDayKeyValue is the natural value of DispensePreparedTimeOfDayKey that you can see without any key decoding

columns.name: AdministeredInstant
columns.description: Date and time the dispense was given to the patient. For Epic data, if a dispense is associated with more than one administration, this is from the first administration. This column isn't populated for outpatient dispenses.

columns.name: DocumentedAdministrationInstant
columns.description: Date and time the dispense was documented as being administered by the administering user. For Epic data, if a dispense is associated with more than one administration, this is from the first administration. This column isn't populated for outpatient dispenses.

columns.name: DispenseSentDateKeyValue
columns.description: Date the dispense was sent; DispenseSentDateKeyValue is the natural value of DispenseSentDateKey that you can see without any key decoding

columns.name: ScheduledDueInstant
columns.description: Date and time when the administration was due. For Epic data, if a dispense is associated with more than one administration, this is from the first administration. This column isn't populated for outpatient dispenses.

columns.name: AdministeredOnTimeStatus
columns.description: Shows whether the administration associated with the dispense was given on time, early, or late. For Epic data, this is not applicable if timeliness is not relevant (e.g. the order frequency is PRN). The status is unknown for administrations documented prior to upgrading to the Epic 2014 version.  This column isn't populated for outpatient dispenses.

columns.name: DispenseSentTimeOfDayKeyValue
columns.description: Time of day the dispense was sent; DispenseSentTimeOfDayKeyValue is the natural value of DispenseSentTimeOfDayKey that you can see without any key decoding

columns.name: ChargeAmount
columns.description: Total amount charged for the dispense

columns.name: MedicationAcquisitionCost
columns.description: Total medication acquisition cost for the dispense

columns.name: DispenseReceivedDateKeyValue
columns.description: Date the dispense was received; DispenseReceivedDateKeyValue is the natural value of DispenseReceivedDateKey that you can see without any key decoding

columns.name: MedicationRepresentativeCost
columns.description: Total medication representative cost for the dispense

columns.name: PatientChargedAmount
columns.description: Total amount charged to the patient. For Epic data, this column isn't populated for inpatient dispenses.

columns.name: DispenseReceivedTimeOfDayKeyValue
columns.description: Time of day the dispense was received; DispenseReceivedTimeOfDayKeyValue is the natural value of DispenseReceivedTimeOfDayKey that you can see without any key decoding

columns.name: PatientPaidAmount
columns.description: Total amount paid by the patient. For Epic data, this column isn't populated for inpatient dispenses.

columns.name: FirstPayorChargedAmount
columns.description: Total amount charged to the first payer. For Epic data, this column isn't populated for inpatient dispenses.

columns.name: FirstPayorPaidAmount
columns.description: Total amount paid by the first payer. For Epic data, this column isn't populated for inpatient dispenses.

columns.name: SecondPayorChargedAmount
columns.description: Total amount charged to the second payer. For Epic data, this column isn't populated for inpatient dispenses.

columns.name: SecondPayorPaidAmount
columns.description: Total amount paid by the second payer. For Epic data, this column isn't populated for inpatient dispenses.

columns.name: ThirdPayorChargedAmount
columns.description: Total amount charged to the third payer. For Epic data, this column isn't populated for inpatient dispenses.

columns.name: ThirdPayorPaidAmount
columns.description: Total amount paid by the third payer. For Epic data, this column isn't populated for inpatient dispenses.

columns.name: PrimaryComponentQuantity
columns.description: Quantity of the primary component dispensed

columns.name: SecondComponentQuantity
columns.description: Quantity of the second component dispensed. For Epic data, this column isn't populated for outpatient dispenses.

columns.name: FirstCoverageFinancialClass
columns.description: Financial class of the coverage; FirstCoverageFinancialClass comes from table CoverageDim, column CoverageFinancialClass by joining on key FirstCoverageKey

columns.name: ThirdComponentQuantity
columns.description: Quantity of the third component dispensed. For Epic data, this column isn't populated for outpatient dispenses.

columns.name: FourthComponentQuantity
columns.description: Quantity of the fourth component dispensed. For Epic data, this column isn't populated for outpatient dispenses.

columns.name: SecondCoverageFinancialClass
columns.description: Financial class of the coverage; SecondCoverageFinancialClass comes from table CoverageDim, column CoverageFinancialClass by joining on key SecondCoverageKey

columns.name: FifthComponentQuantity
columns.description: Quantity of the fifth component dispensed. For Epic data, this column isn't populated for outpatient dispenses.

columns.name: DaysSupply
columns.description: Number of days supply dispensed of the medication. For Epic data, this column isn't populated for inpatient dispenses.

columns.name: ThirdCoverageFinancialClass
columns.description: Financial class of the coverage; ThirdCoverageFinancialClass comes from table CoverageDim, column CoverageFinancialClass by joining on key ThirdCoverageKey

columns.name: FillNumber
columns.description: The fill number for the current dispensed medication by the pharmacy. Designates the sequential order of the original fill or subsequent refills of a prescription. For Epic data, this column isn't populated for inpatient dispenses.

columns.name: RxNumber
columns.description: The formatted prescription number for the dispense. For Epic data, this column isn't populated for inpatient dispenses.

columns.name: ForcedDispense
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the dispense was forced. This column returns 1 if the dispense was forced and 0 if the dispense wasn't forced. For Epic data, this indicates if the dispense was an override pull for inpatient dispenses.

columns.name: ForcedDispenseResolved
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the forced dispense was resolved. This column returns 1 if a forced dispense was resolved and 0 if it was not resolved. For Epic data, this column indicates if an ADS override pull was linked to a clinical order. This column isn’t populated for dispenses that are outpatient or not forced.

columns.name: ReturnedDispense
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the dispense was returned. This column returns 1 if the dispense was returned and 0 if the dispense wasn't returned.

columns.name: AdsDispense
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the dispense is from an automated dispense system. This column returns 1 if the dispense is from an automated dispense system and 0 if the dispense isn't from an automated dispense system.

columns.name: CartDispense
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the dispense is from a cart. This column returns 1 if the dispense is from a cart and 0 if the dispense isn't from a cart. For Epic data, this column isn't populated for outpatient dispenses.

columns.name: FirstDispense
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the dispense is a first dose or fill. This column returns 1 if the dispense is a first dose or fill and 0 if the dispense isn't a first dose or fill.

columns.name: Redispense
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the dispense is a redispense. This column returns 1 if the dispense is a redispense and 0 if the dispense isn't a redispense. For Epic data, this column isn't populated for outpatient dispenses.

columns.name: BulkDispense
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the dispense is a bulk product dispense. This column returns 1 if the dispense is a bulk product dispense and 0 if the dispense isn't a bulk product dispense. For Epic data, this column isn't populated for outpatient dispenses.

columns.name: PreparationCompleted
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether a dispense was documented as prepared. This column returns 1 if dispense preparation was documented and 0 if it was not documented. For Epic data, this column isn't populated for outpatient dispenses.

columns.name: PreparationNearMiss
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the user was shown a warning and the user canceled the action, potentially preventing a medication error. This column returns 1 if a near miss occurred and 0 if there was not a near miss for this dispense.  For Epic data, this column isn't populated for outpatient dispenses.

columns.name: WrongIngredientWarningDuringPreparation
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the user was warned that they were preparing the dispense with the wrong ingredient. This column returns 1 if a warning of this type was shown and 0 if one was not shown.  For Epic data, this column isn't populated for outpatient dispenses.

columns.name: WrongIngredientWarningOverrideDuringPreparation
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the user overrode a warning that they were preparing the dispense with the wrong ingredient. This column returns 1 if the warning was overridden and 0 if the user did not override the warning. For Epic data, this column isn't populated for outpatient dispenses or if no wrong ingredient warning was encountered.

columns.name: ExpiredProductWarningDuringPreparation
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the user was warned that the medications were past their expiration date during dispense preparation. This column returns 1 if a warning of this type was shown and 0 if one was not shown.  For Epic data, this column isn't populated for outpatient dispenses.

columns.name: MedicationScannedForDispense
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the dispensed medication was scanned. This column returns 1 if the dispensed medication was scanned and 0 if the dispensed medication wasn't scanned. For Epic data, this column isn't populated for outpatient dispenses.

columns.name: InactiveWarningDuringPreparation
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the user was warned that the dispense no longer needs to be prepared during dispense preparation. This column returns 1 if a warning of this type was shown and 0 if one was not shown.  For Epic data, this column isn't populated for outpatient dispenses.

columns.name: BarcodeNotRecognizedWarningDuringPreparation
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the user was warned that the barcode was not recognized during dispense preparation. This column returns 1 if a warning of this type was shown and 0 if one was not shown.  For Epic data, this column isn't populated for outpatient dispenses.

columns.name: MedicationAttemptedToScanForDispense
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the dispensed medication was attempted to be scanned. This column returns 1 if the dispensed medication was attempted to be scanned and 0 if the dispensed medication wasn't attempted to be scanned. For Epic data, this column isn't populated for outpatient dispenses.

columns.name: NdcManuallyEntered
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the National Drug Code (NDC) was manually entered. This column returns 1 if the NDC was manually entered and 0 if the NDC wasn't manually entered. For Epic data, this column isn't populated for outpatient dispenses.

columns.name: PendingDispense
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the dispense is pending. This column returns 1 if the dispense is pending and 0 if the dispense isn't pending.

columns.name: Rejected
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the dispense was rejected while being checked, before it was sent to the patient. This column returns 1 if the dispense was rejected during dispense check and 0 if the dispense was not rejected. For Epic data, this column isn't populated for outpatient dispenses.

columns.name: Canceled
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether a dispense was canceled. For Epic data, a dispense can be canceled if it is rejected in Dispense Check or if the order is edited before release and the dispense was prepared in advance. This column returns 1 if the dispense was canceled and 0 if the dispense was not canceled. This column isn't populated for outpatient dispenses.

columns.name: Count
columns.description: Artificial measure on which calculations can be done. The value is 0 for rows marked as deleted, 1 otherwise.

columns.name: IntendedQuantityUnit
columns.description: Intended quantity unit of this medication dispense. For Epic data, this column is not populated for inpatient dispenses.

columns.name: IntendedQuantity
columns.description: Intended quantity of this medication dispense. For Epic data, this column is not populated for inpatient dispenses.

MedicationOrderFact.description: The medication order fact contains information about medication orders. Each row represents an order.  For Epic data, this fact excludes historical orders and bulk dispense orders.; NOTE: 7/21/2014 TAS: MedicationOrderFact matches the count of Clarity's ORDER_METRICS as INNER JOIN'ed to ORDER_MED on the ORDER_MED_ID as the ORDER_ID.  Over time, if rows are deleted from this Clarity result, the rows are retained in the Warehouse with attributes keyed as -3.  The difference of deleted rows in Clarity matches that of the deleted rows remaining in the Warehouse.

columns.name: MedicationOrderKey

columns.name: DeidLds

columns.name: PatientDurableKey

columns.name: EncounterKey

columns.name: DepartmentName

columns.name: MedicationKey

columns.name: AssociatedDiagnosisComboKey

For Epic data, this column can contain Standard, Automated Dispensing Station, Robotic Dispensing System, Automated Prescription Filling System, or other values.; PharmacyPhysicalType comes from table PharmacyDim, column PhysicalType by joining on key PharmacyKey

columns.name: OrderedByProviderKey
columns.description: Provider who is responsible for the order. For Epic data, this column is rarely populated for outpatient orders.

columns.name: OrderedByProviderDurableKey
columns.description: Provider who is responsible for the order. For Epic data, this column is rarely populated for outpatient orders.

columns.name: PharmacyFacilityAdministeredMedicationsSupported
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the pharmacy supports facility administered medications. This column returns 1 if the pharmacy supports facility administered medications and 0 if the pharmacy doesn't support facility administered medications.; PharmacyFacilityAdministeredMedicationsSupported comes from table PharmacyDim, column FacilityAdministeredMedicationsSupported by joining on key PharmacyKey

columns.name: PharmacyPrescriptionsSupported
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the pharmacy supports prescriptions. This column returns 1 if the pharmacy supports prescriptions and 0 if the pharmacy doesn't support prescriptions.; PharmacyPrescriptionsSupported comes from table PharmacyDim, column PrescriptionsSupported by joining on key PharmacyKey

columns.name: MedicationGenericName
columns.description: Generic, non-proprietary name of the medication. For Epic data, if the medication has multiple generic names, this is the first name listed.; MedicationGenericName comes from table MedicationDim, column GenericName by joining on key MedicationKey

columns.name: MedicationTherapeuticClass
columns.description: Therapeutic class that indicates the accepted purpose of the medication; MedicationTherapeuticClass comes from table MedicationDim, column TherapeuticClass by joining on key MedicationKey

columns.name: FirstVerificationEmployeeKey
columns.description: Employee who did the initial review for new order pharmacy verification. For Epic data, this is the first verify user for an order verified with a dual verify workflow. If the order is conditional, this is the user who reviewed the order before it was initiated. This column is not applicable for outpatient orders.

columns.name: MedicationPharmaceuticalClass
columns.description: Pharmaceutical class that indicates the chemical family the medication belongs to; MedicationPharmaceuticalClass comes from table MedicationDim, column PharmaceuticalClass by joining on key MedicationKey

columns.name: MedicationPharmaceuticalSubclass
columns.description: Pharmaceutical subclass that indicates the chemical family the medication belongs to. For Epic data, if there are multiple subclasses for the medication, this is the first subclass listed.; MedicationPharmaceuticalSubclass comes from table MedicationDim, column PharmaceuticalSubclass by joining on key MedicationKey

columns.name: SecondVerificationEmployeeKey
columns.description: Employee who did the second review of the order during new order pharmacy verification. For Epic data, this is the second verify user for an order verified with a dual verify workflow. This column is not applicable for outpatient orders.

columns.name: MedicationStrength
columns.description: Strength of the medication; MedicationStrength comes from table MedicationDim, column Strength by joining on key MedicationKey

columns.name: FinalVerificationEmployeeKey
columns.description: Employee who completed new order pharmacy verification. For Epic data, if the order was dual verified this is the second verifying user. If the order is conditional this is the verify user after the order is initiated. This column is not applicable for outpatient orders.

columns.name: MedicationForm

columns.description: Epic ID of the medication order. This column identifies order (ORD) records.

columns.name: ReleaseInstant
columns.description: Date and time the new order was released. For Epic data, if the order is conditional, this is the date and time it was initiated. This column is not populated for outpatient orders.

columns.name: FirstVerificationInstant
columns.description: Date and time the new order was first reviewed by pharmacy.  For Epic inpatient data, if the order is dual verified this is the date and time for the first verify. This column is not populated for outpatient orders.

columns.name: SecondVerificationInstant
columns.description: Date and time of the second review of a new order by pharmacy.  For Epic inpatient data, if the order is dual verified this is the date and time for the second verify. This column is not applicable for outpatient orders.

columns.name: FinalVerificationInstant
columns.description: Date and time the new order was rejected or pharmacy verification was completed. For Epic data, this column is not populated for outpatient orders.

columns.name: FinalVerificationOutcome
columns.description: The final outcome during pharmacy verification of a new order. Shows if the order was verified or rejected. For Epic data, this column can return Verified, Rejected, Not Verified, Autoverified, Verified Before Release, Same User Released and Verified, or other values. This column returns Verified or Rejected for orders that populate the MinutesToManualFinalVerification column. If another value is returned, the value includes a description of why the order is not applicable to verification turnaround time. This column is not applicable for outpatient orders.

columns.name: MinutesToFirstDue
columns.description: The number of minutes between when an order is released and when it is first due. For Epic data, this column is not populated for outpatient orders.

columns.name: MinutesToManualFinalVerification
columns.description: The number of minutes between a new order being released and when it is manually verified or rejected by pharmacy review. This column is not populated for orders that are autoverified, verified by the same user who placed the order, or otherwise not applicable to verification turnaround time. For Epic data, this column will return a value only if the FinalVerificationOutcome column returns Verified or Rejected. This column is not populated for outpatient orders.

columns.name: Quantity
columns.description: Quantity of the medication dispensed. For Epic data, this column is not populated for inpatient orders.

columns.name: MinimumDose
columns.description: Minimum ordered dose. For Epic data, if the dose is not ordered as a range, this column can contain the exact dose associated with the order.

columns.name: MaximumDose
columns.description: Maximum ordered dose. For Epic data, if the dose is not ordered as a range, this column is empty.

columns.name: CalculatedMinimumDose
columns.description: Minimum calculated dose. For Epic data, if the dose is not ordered as a range, this column can contain the calculated exact dose associated with the order.

columns.name: CalculatedMaximumDose
columns.description: Maximum calculated dose. For Epic data, if the dose is not ordered as a range, this column is empty.

columns.name: NumberOfDoses
columns.description: Total number of doses that should be given to the patient

columns.name: RefillsWritten
columns.description: Number of refills ordered. For Epic data, this column is not populated for inpatient orders.

columns.name: Sig
columns.description: Patient directions for use as ordered. For Epic data, this column is not populated for inpatient orders.

columns.name: Cpoe
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the order was submitted via a computerized physician order entry (CPOE), based on comparing the ordering provider to the ordering user. This column returns 1 if the order was submitted using CPOE and 0 if the order wasn't submitted using CPOE.

columns.name: DispenseAsWritten
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the order should be dispensed as written for the medication. This column returns 1 if the order should be dispensed as written for the medication and 0 if the order shouldn't be dispensed as written for the medication. For Epic data, this column is not populated for inpatient orders.

columns.name: OrderedAsNonFormulary
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the medication was ordered as non-formulary. This column returns 1 if the medication was ordered as non-formulary and 0 if the medication was ordered from the formulary. For Epic data, this column is not populated for outpatient orders.

columns.name: VerifiedAsNonFormulary
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the medication was verified as non-formulary. This column returns 1 if the medication was verified as non-formulary and 0 if the medication was verified as part of the formulary. For Epic data, this column is not populated for outpatient orders.

columns.name: AutomaticallyVerified
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the order was automatically verified. This column returns 1 if the order was automatically verified and 0 if the order wasn't automatically verified. For Epic data, this column is not populated for outpatient orders.

columns.name: PharmacyInterventionPriorToVerify
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether a pharmacist performed clinical investigation or got clarification prior to verifying the order. This column returns 1 if an intervention is created for the order before the order is verified or rejected and 0 if an intervention was not created before verification was complete. For Epic data, this column is not populated for outpatient orders.

columns.name: ReorderedFromPrescription
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether an inpatient medication order is reordered from a prescription. This column returns 1 if the order is reordered from a prescription and 0 if not reordered from a prescription. For Epic data, this column is not populated for outpatient orders.

columns.name: Verbal
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the medication order is a verbal order. This column returns 1 if the medication order is a verbal order and 0 if the medication order isn't a verbal order.

columns.name: RequiresCosign
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the medication order requires a cosign. This column returns 1 if the medication order requires a cosign and 0 if the medication order doesn't require a cosign.

columns.name: Cosigned
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the medication order was cosigned. This column returns 1 if the medication order was cosigned and 0 if the medication order wasn't cosigned. For Epic data, this column is only populated for standard (non-verbal) orders.

columns.name: VerbalSigned
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the medication order was verbally signed. This column returns 1 if the medication order was verbally signed and 0 if the medication order wasn't verbally signed.

columns.name: Protocol
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the medication order is a protocol order. This column returns 1 if the medication order is a protocol order and 0 if the medication order isn't a protocol order.

columns.name: HighPriority
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates if this a high priority order. This column returns 1 if the order is high priority and 0 if not high priority.

columns.name: Prn
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates if the order is given as needed. Returns 1 if order is given as needed and 0 if ordered without a PRN frequency.

columns.name: Count
columns.description: Artificial measure on which calculations can be done. The value is 0 for rows marked as deleted, 1 otherwise.

columns.name: SupervisedByProviderDurableKey
columns.description: Provider under whose supervision the order was placed

PatientLocationEventFact.description: The patient location event fact contains information about where a patient was located at a given point in time during an encounter. For hospital stays, each row represents a patient's location for a given period of time. For outpatient encounters, each row represents a department.  For Epic data, this fact includes information from admissions, transfers, patient location updates, and outpatient encounters.

PregnancyFact.description: The pregnancy fact contains information about pregnancies. Each row represents a patient's pregnancy.

columns.name: PregnancyKey
columns.description: Surrogate key used to uniquely identify the record

columns.name: PatientKey
columns.description: Patient who is pregnant

columns.name: EpisodeKey
columns.description: Pregnancy episode

columns.name: WorkingEstimatedDateOfDeliveryKey
columns.description: Working estimated date of delivery for the pregnancy

columns.name: EpisodeStartDateKey
columns.description: Date the clinician created the pregnancy episode. Note that this is not the date the pregnancy began. For historical pregnancy episodes, this is the day that the pregnancy was added to the patient's obstetric history.

columns.name: EpisodeEndDateKey
columns.description: Date the clinician resolved the pregnancy episode. Note that this is not the delivery date. For historical pregnancy episodes, this does not have a value.

columns.name: LastDeliveryDateKey
columns.description: Date of the last delivery for the pregnancy. If a fuzzy date was documented, this is the earliest date that the fuzzy date could represent. The LastDeliveryDateConfidentToYear, LastDeliveryDateConfidentToMonth, LastDeliveryDateConfidentToDate, and LastDeliveryDateConfidentToTime columns indicate whether a fuzzy date was documented and at what level of confidence.

columns.name: LastDeliveryTimeOfDayKey
columns.description: Time of day of the last delivery for the pregnancy. If the last delivery date is any less confident than to the time, this is the UTC representation of midnight in the time zone of the encounter that the delivery was documented.

columns.name: PregnancyEstimatedStartDateKey
columns.description: Estimated start date for the pregnancy. If an estimated date of delivery is documented, this will be 280 days prior to that date. Otherwise if a gestational age for the last delivery is documented and the last delivery date is at least confident to the month, this will be the last delivery date subtracted by the gestational age. Otherwise if the pregnancy is not historical, this will be the episode start date. Otherwise this will be NULL.

columns.name: PregnancyEpicId
columns.description: Epic ID of the pregnancy. This column identifies pregnancy (HSB) records.

columns.name: PregravidWeight
columns.description: Patient's weight prior to pregnancy in ounces

columns.name: PregravidBmi
columns.description: Patient's body mass index prior to pregnancy

columns.name: NumberOfFetuses
columns.description: Total number of fetuses involved in this pregnancy

columns.name: PregnancyGravidaCount
columns.description: Gravida count as of this pregnancy. This pregnancy is included in the count.

columns.name: PregnancyParaCount
columns.description: Para count as of this pregnancy. This pregnancy is not included in the count.

columns.name: PregnancyTermCount
columns.description: Term count as of this pregnancy. This pregnancy is not included in the count.

columns.name: PregnancyPretermCount
columns.description: Preterm count as of this pregnancy. This pregnancy is not included in the count.

columns.name: PregnancyAbortionCount
columns.description: Abortion count as of this pregnancy. This pregnancy is not included in the count.

columns.name: PregnancyTherapeuticAbortionCount
columns.description: Induced abortion count as of this pregnancy (previously referred to as therapeutic abortion count). This pregnancy is not included in the count.

columns.name: PregnancySpontaneousAbortionCount
columns.description: Spontaneous abortion count as of this pregnancy. This pregnancy is not included in the count.

columns.name: PregnancyEctopicCount
columns.description: Ectopic count as of this pregnancy. This pregnancy is not included in the count.

columns.name: PregnancyPriorLiveBirthCount
columns.description: Live birth count as of this pregnancy. This pregnancy's outcomes are not included in the count.

columns.name: LastDeliveryGestationalAge
columns.description: Gestational age in days for the last delivery for the pregnancy, based on OB History documentation.

columns.name: PriorCesarean
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the patient had a cesarean delivery prior to this pregnancy. This column returns 1 if they have a prior outcome in their obstetric history with a cesarean delivery method, 0 if none of their prior outcomes have a cesarean delivery method, and NULL if they have no prior outcomes.

columns.name: IsHistorical
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether this pregnancy is a historical pregnancy documented directly in the patient's obstetric history. This column returns 1 if the pregnancy is historical, and 0 if it is a regular pregnancy.

columns.name: LastDeliveryDateConfidentToYear
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates if the last delivery date and time are only confident to the year. This column returns 1 if they are only confident to the year, 0 if they are confident to another level, and NULL if no delivery date was found.

columns.name: LastDeliveryDateConfidentToMonth
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates if the last delivery date and time are only confident to the month. This column returns 1 if they are only confident to the month, 0 if they are confident to another level, and NULL if no delivery date was found.

columns.name: LastDeliveryDateConfidentToDate
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates if the last delivery date and time are only confident to the date. This column returns 1 if they are only confident to the date, 0 if they are confident to another level, and NULL if no delivery date was found.

columns.name: LastDeliveryDateConfidentToTime
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates if the last delivery date and time are fully confident. This column returns 1 if they are fully confident, 0 if they are confident to another level, and NULL if no delivery date was found.

columns.name: Count
columns.description: Artificial measure on which calculations can be done. The value is 0 for rows marked as deleted, 1 otherwise.

columns.name: _IsInferred
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the record is inferred

columns.name: _IsDeleted
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the record is deleted

columns.name: PregnancyEstimatedEndDateKey
columns.description: The estimated end date for the pregnancy. This is the last delivery date if it is confident to at least the month. Otherwise, this is the episode end date if it is less than 28 days after the working estimated delivery date (EDD) or before the working EDD or within 308 days of the episode start if the working EDD is not documented. Otherwise, this is the working EDD plus 28 days if it is documented. Otherwise, this is the episode start date plus 308 days if it is not a historical pregnancy. Otherwise, this is -1.

columns.name: HighestPostpartumEncounterEdinburghSelfHarmVal

columns.name: FirstDeliveryEncounterModifiedBishopScore
columns.description: This column is not populated because it was misnamed from the outset; use FirstDeliveryEncounterSimplifiedBishopScore

columns.description: The count of the pregnancy's prenatal encounters that occurred at this organization

columns.name: OrganizationPostpartumEncounterCount
columns.description: The count of the pregnancy's postpartum encounters that occurred at this organization

columns.name: QuantitativeBloodLossMl
columns.description: The quantitative blood loss for the delivery and postpartum period in milliliters

columns.name: DeliverySevereHypertensionBloodPressureRetaken
columns.description: 1/0/NULL column that finds the first blood pressure reading on the delivery encounter with a blood pressure reading greater than or equal to either 160 systolic or 110 diastolic. This column returns 1 if there was another blood pressure reading taken within 15 minutes after that reading, 0 if no blood pressure reading was taken within 15 minutes after that reading, and NULL if no blood pressure readings greater than or equal to either 160 systolic or 110 diastolic were found.

columns.name: DeliveryHypertensiveEmergencyStartDateKey
columns.description: Date when the hypertensive emergency began on the delivery encounter.  A hypertensive emergency is the first time on an encounter when two blood pressures greater than or equal to either 160 systolic or 110 diastolic are documented between 15 and 60 minutes of each other. The emergency begins at the time of the second of the two blood pressures.

columns.name: DeliveryHypertensiveEmergencyStartTimeOfDayKey
columns.description: Time of day when the hypertensive emergency began on the delivery encounter.  A hypertensive emergency is the first time on an encounter when two blood pressures greater than or equal to either 160 systolic or 110 diastolic are documented between 15 and 60 minutes of each other. The emergency begins at the time of the second of the two blood pressures.

columns.name: DeliveryHypertensiveEmergencyStartInstant
columns.description: Date and time when the hypertensive emergency began on the delivery encounter.  A hypertensive emergency is the first time on an encounter when two blood pressures greater than or equal to either 160 systolic or 110 diastolic are documented between 15 and 60 minutes of each other. The emergency begins at the time of the second of the two blood pressures.

columns.name: DeliveryHypertensiveTreatmentStartDateKey
columns.description: Date when a hypertensive emergency treatment medication was first administered on the delivery encounter.  For patients that had a hypertensive emergency, treatment could have been initiated at any point after the first of the two blood pressures that were greater than or equal to either 160 systolic or 110 diastolic that were documented between 15 and 60 minutes of each other. If a hypertensive emergency treatment medication was administered between the two flowsheet times, treatment could begin before the emergency start time.

columns.name: DeliveryHypertensiveTreatmentStartTimeOfDayKey
columns.description: Time of day when a hypertensive emergency treatment medication was first administered on the delivery encounter.  For patients that had a hypertensive emergency, treatment could have been initiated at any point after the first of the two blood pressures that were greater than or equal to either 160 systolic or 110 diastolic that were documented between 15 and 60 minutes of each other. If a hypertensive emergency treatment medication was administered between the two flowsheet times, treatment could begin before the emergency start time.

columns.name: DeliveryHypertensiveTreatmentStartInstant
columns.description: Date and time when a hypertensive emergency treatment medication was first administered on the delivery encounter.  For patients that had a hypertensive emergency, treatment could have been initiated at any point after the first of the two blood pressures that were greater than or equal to either 160 systolic or 110 diastolic that were documented between 15 and 60 minutes of each other. If a hypertensive emergency treatment medication was administered between the two flowsheet times, treatment could begin before the emergency start time.

columns.name: _IsInferred
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the record is inferred

columns.name: _IsDeleted
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the record is deleted

columns.name: FirstDeliveryEncounterSimplifiedBishopScore
columns.description: The first Simplified Bishop Score from the pregnancy's labor and delivery encounter

columns.name: IntrapartumBloodLossMl
columns.description: The total blood loss for the intrapartum period. Intrapartum blood loss is calculated starting from the earliest labor onset instant for the pregnancy if there is one, otherwise the procedure start instant from the associated case if there is one, or otherwise it will start from twelve hours prior to the earliest delivery instant for the pregnancy. Calculation ends at the latest delivery instant for the pregnancy.

columns.name: PostpartumBloodLossMl
columns.description: The total blood loss for the postpartum period. Postpartum blood loss is calculated from the 24 hours following the latest delivery instant for the pregnancy.

columns.name: TotalBloodLossMl
columns.description: The total combined intrapartum and postpartum blood loss. Total blood loss is calculated starting from the earliest labor onset instant for the pregnancy if there is one, otherwise the procedure start instant from the associated case if there is one, or otherwise it will start from twelve hours prior to the earliest delivery instant for the pregnancy. Calculation ends 24 hours after the latest delivery instant for the pregnancy.

columns.name: VteDiagnosed
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the patient was diagnosed with VTE during the pregnancy. This column returns 1 if the patient was diagnosed during the pregnancy and returns 0 otherwise.

columns.name: DeliveryEncounterTransfusionUnits
columns.description: The number of units of blood transfused on the mother during the delivery encounter. Transfusions administered in something other than units (such as pools) will be included as if they were administered in units

For Epic data, this fact excludes most child orders (child orders related to Anesthesia procedures are included), pended orders, orders created through an interface, and historical orders. ; NOTE: 7/21/2014 TAS: ProcedureOrderFact matches the count of Clarity's ORDER_METRICS as INNER JOIN'ed to ORDER_PROC on the ORDER_PROC_ID as the ORDER_ID. ProviderDim.description: The provider dimension contains information about providers. Each row represents a provider for a date range.  This table contains both current and historical information. For current records, IsCurrent has a value of 1. Historical records contain information that is valid for the date range specified by the StartDate and EndDate columns.; NOTE: Heed the Epic note!  "...the dimension includes only staff" means that only CLARITY_SER rows where the resource type is PERSON will count as valid for a ProviderDim row.  Thus, if any related Warehouse fact table has an undefined provider, it may be that Clarity contains a provider, but that provider is not a specific Person.

columns.name: Accepted
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the referral has been accepted. This column returns 1 if the referral has been accepted and 0 if the referral hasn't been accepted.

columns.name: Rejected
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the referral has been rejected. This column returns 1 if the referral has been rejected and 0 if the referral hasn't been rejected.

columns.name: Redirected
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the referral was ever redirected. This column returns 1 if the referral was ever redirected and 0 if the referral was never redirected.

columns.name: GeneratedByOrder
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the referral was generated by an order. This column returns 1 if the referral was generated by an order and 0 if the referral wasn't generated by an order.

columns.name: InAnyWorkqueue
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the referral is currently in a workqueue. This column returns 1 if the referral is currently in a workqueue and 0 if the referral isn't currently in a workqueue.

columns.name: IsInternal
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the referral is internal. This column returns 1 if the referral is internal and 0 if the referral isn't internal.

columns.name: LinkedToAnEncounter
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the referral is associated with an encounter. This column returns 1 if the referral is associated with an encounter and 0 if the referral isn't associated with an encounter.

columns.name: IsLeaked
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the referral is considered leaked. This column returns 1 if the referral is considered leaked, 0 if the referral is considered retained, and NULL otherwise.

columns.name: AuthorizedThroughAutoStatusAssignment
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the referral was authorized through Auto Status Assignment. This column returns 1 if the referral was authorized by Auto Status Assignment and 0 if it was not.

columns.name: IsComplete
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the referral is considered complete. This column returns 1 if the referral is complete and 0 if the referral is not considered complete.

columns.name: IsLoopClosed
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the loop is closed for the referral. This column returns 1 if the loop is closed and 0 if it is not.

columns.name: Count
columns.description: Artificial measure on which calculations can be done. The value is 0 for rows marked as deleted, 1 otherwise.

columns.name: _IsInferred
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the record is inferred

columns.name: _IsDeleted
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the record is deleted

columns.name: ReferredToProviderSpecialtyCategoryKey
columns.description: Category associated with the referred to provider's specialty

columns.name: ReferredToDepartmentSpecialtyCategoryKey
columns.description: Category associated with the referred to department's specialty

RegistryMetricDim.description: The registry metric dimension contains information about metrics used in registries. Each row represents a metric for a registry.   For Epic data, each registry has one derived row for its membership status.

columns.name: RegistryMetricKey
columns.description: Surrogate key used to uniquely identify the record

columns.name: DeidLds
columns.description: Shows 'DEID' if this is de-identified data and 'LDS' if this is a Limited Data Set

columns.name: RegistryEpicId
columns.description: Epic Id of the registry. This column identifies registry (HFR) records.

columns.name: RegistryName
columns.description: Name of the registry

columns.name: MetricEpicId
columns.description: Epic Id of the metric. This column identifies registry metric rule (CER) records.

columns.name: MetricName
columns.description: Name of the metric

columns.name: MetricValueType
columns.description: Type of the value for the associated metric. For Epic data, this column can hold the following values: Benefit Plan, Delimited Data, Department, Diagnosis, Location, Networked, Payor, Provider, String, and Surgical Log.

columns.name: IsMetricEnabled
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether a metric is enabled or disabled. This column returns 1 if the metric is enabled, 0 if it is disabled, and NULL otherwise.

columns.name: IsMetricExternal
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the metric is an external metric or not. This column returns 1 if the metric is an external metric, 0 if it is internal, and NULL otherwise.

VisitFact.description: The visit fact contains information about visits. Each row represents a visit encounter.  For Epic data, the fact includes appointment records as well as records with encounter types configured in Chronicles as face-to-face. The full list of encounter types is displayed in Component Configuration.; NOTE: 6/5 TAS: VisitFact Outpatient (IdType EpicEncounterCsnId:Outpatient) records are selected using PAT_ENC.ENC_TYPE_C IN (2, 50, 101, 108).   This is a fraction of the contact types recorded in the universe of all encounters.  These are the Appointments, Office Visits, Immunizations, and Walk-Ins referred to in the verbiage above by Epic.  UCSF has no Walk-In encounters.  UCSF may add additional Contact Types (EPT/30, maintained in CLARITY..ZC_DISP_ENC_TYPE) to the logic for VisitFact Outpatient if we wish.  However, only those types which are not Epic Released can be used.  Those are all types whose ID (ENC_TYPE_C) is not 0 - 119 or 150.
