columns.name: PrimaryDiagnosisKey
columns.description: Primary encounter diagnosis for the visit

columns.name: EncounterDiagnosisComboKey
columns.description: All encounter diagnoses for the visit

columns.name: CheckInDateKeyValue
columns.description: Date when the patient was checked in; CheckInDateKeyValue is the natural value of CheckInDateKey that you can see without any key decoding

columns.name: PrimaryVisitProviderKey
columns.description: Primary visit provider for the visit

columns.name: PrimaryVisitProviderDurableKey
columns.description: Primary visit provider for the visit

columns.name: CheckInTimeOfDayKeyValue
columns.description: Time of day when the patient was checked in; CheckInTimeOfDayKeyValue is the natural value of CheckInTimeOfDayKey that you can see without any key decoding

columns.name: SecondVisitProviderKey
columns.description: Second visit provider for the visit

columns.name: RoomedDateKeyValue
columns.description: Date when the patient was roomed; RoomedDateKeyValue is the natural value of RoomedDateKey that you can see without any key decoding

columns.name: SecondVisitProviderDurableKey
columns.description: Second visit provider for the visit

columns.name: RoomedTimeOfDayKeyValue
columns.description: Time of day when the patient was roomed; RoomedTimeOfDayKeyValue is the natural value of RoomedTimeOfDayKey that you can see without any key decoding

columns.name: ThirdVisitProviderKey
columns.description: Third visit provider for the visit

columns.name: ThirdVisitProviderDurableKey
columns.description: Third visit provider for the visit

columns.name: CheckOutDateKeyValue
columns.description: Date when the patient was checked out; CheckOutDateKeyValue is the natural value of CheckOutDateKey that you can see without any key decoding

columns.name: FourthVisitProviderKey
columns.description: Fourth visit provider for the visit

columns.name: CheckOutTimeOfDayKeyValue
columns.description: Time of day when the patient was checked out; CheckOutTimeOfDayKeyValue is the natural value of CheckOutTimeOfDayKey that you can see without any key decoding

columns.name: FourthVisitProviderDurableKey
columns.description: Fourth visit provider for the visit

columns.name: BedName
columns.description: Name of the bed; BedName comes from table DepartmentDim, column BedName by joining on key DepartmentKey

columns.name: DepartmentName
columns.description: Name of the department or submitter; DepartmentName comes from table DepartmentDim, column DepartmentName by joining on key DepartmentKey

columns.name: DepartmentSpecialty
columns.description: Specialty practiced in the department; DepartmentSpecialty comes from table DepartmentDim, column DepartmentSpecialty by joining on key DepartmentKey

columns.name: PrimaryResourceKey
columns.description: Scheduled resource for the visit

columns.name: PrimaryDiagnosisName
columns.description: Diagnosis name; PrimaryDiagnosisName comes from table DiagnosisDim, column Name by joining on key PrimaryDiagnosisKey

columns.name: LevelOfServiceAuthorizedByProviderKey
columns.description: Provider who authorized the level of service for the visit

columns.name: LevelOfServiceAuthorizedByProviderDurableKey
columns.description: Provider who authorized the level of service for the visit

columns.name: PrimaryVisitProviderType
columns.description: Type of the provider; PrimaryVisitProviderType comes from table ProviderDim, column Type by joining on key PrimaryVisitProviderKey

columns.name: PrimaryVisitProviderPrimarySpecialty
columns.description: Primary specialty of the provider; PrimaryVisitProviderPrimarySpecialty comes from table ProviderDim, column PrimarySpecialty by joining on key PrimaryVisitProviderKey

columns.name: EncounterClosedByProviderKey
columns.description: Provider who closed the encounter

columns.name: EncounterClosedByProviderDurableKey
columns.description: Provider who closed the encounter

columns.name: GuarantorKey
columns.description: Guarantor associated with the visit

columns.name: SecondVisitProviderType
columns.description: Type of the provider; SecondVisitProviderType comes from table ProviderDim, column Type by joining on key SecondVisitProviderKey

columns.name: SecondVisitProviderPrimarySpecialty
columns.description: Primary specialty of the provider; SecondVisitProviderPrimarySpecialty comes from table ProviderDim, column PrimarySpecialty by joining on key SecondVisitProviderKey

columns.name: CoverageKey
columns.description: Coverage for the visit. For Epic data, this column stores the primary coverage on the associated hospital account if it is available. Otherwise it stores the original coverage on the first non-voided professional transaction if it is available. Otherwise it stores the coverage assigned at check-in or appointment entry.

columns.name: EncounterType
columns.description: Encounter type for the visit. For Epic data, hospital outpatient visits are indicated by a type of Hospital Encounter.

columns.name: VisitType
columns.description: Visit type for the visit

columns.name: ThirdVisitProviderType
columns.description: Type of the provider; ThirdVisitProviderType comes from table ProviderDim, column Type by joining on key ThirdVisitProviderKey

columns.name: ThirdVisitProviderPrimarySpecialty
columns.description: Primary specialty of the provider; ThirdVisitProviderPrimarySpecialty comes from table ProviderDim, column PrimarySpecialty by joining on key ThirdVisitProviderKey

columns.name: FinancialClass
columns.description: This column should no longer be used and will be removed in a future version. As a replacement, use CoverageDim.PayorFinancialClass.

columns.name: AppointmentStatus
columns.description: Status of the appointment

columns.name: SystolicBloodPressure
columns.description: Patient systolic blood pressure for the visit

columns.name: FourthVisitProviderType
columns.description: Type of the provider; FourthVisitProviderType comes from table ProviderDim, column Type by joining on key FourthVisitProviderKey

columns.name: FourthVisitProviderPrimarySpecialty
columns.description: Primary specialty of the provider; FourthVisitProviderPrimarySpecialty comes from table ProviderDim, column PrimarySpecialty by joining on key FourthVisitProviderKey

columns.name: AppointmentConfirmationStatus
columns.description: Confirmation status of the appointment

columns.name: AppointmentLengthInMinutes
columns.description: Length of the scheduled appointment in minutes

columns.name: AppointmentLeadTimeInDays
columns.description: Number of days from the appointment creation date to the appointment date. By default, this is calculated from AppointmentCreationDate and AppointmentInstant.

columns.name: PrimaryResourceName
columns.description: Name of the resource; PrimaryResourceName comes from table ResourceDim, column Name by joining on key PrimaryResourceKey

columns.name: PrimaryResourceModality
columns.description: Modality associated with the resource; PrimaryResourceModality comes from table ResourceDim, column Modality by joining on key PrimaryResourceKey

columns.name: LevelOfServiceAuthorizedByProviderType
columns.description: Type of the provider; LevelOfServiceAuthorizedByProviderType comes from table ProviderDim, column Type by joining on key LevelOfServiceAuthorizedByProviderKey

columns.name: LevelOfServiceAuthorizedByProviderPrimarySpecialty
columns.description: Primary specialty of the provider; LevelOfServiceAuthorizedByProviderPrimarySpecialty comes from table ProviderDim, column PrimarySpecialty by joining on key LevelOfServiceAuthorizedByProviderKey

columns.name: EncounterClosedByProviderType
columns.description: Type of the provider; EncounterClosedByProviderType comes from table ProviderDim, column Type by joining on key EncounterClosedByProviderKey

columns.name: EncounterClosedByProviderPrimarySpecialty
columns.description: Primary specialty of the provider; EncounterClosedByProviderPrimarySpecialty comes from table ProviderDim, column PrimarySpecialty by joining on key EncounterClosedByProviderKey

columns.name: ReasonAppointmentCanceled
columns.description: Reason for the appointment cancellation, if the appointment was canceled

columns.name: NoShowPredictedProbability
columns.description: The most recent percent likelihood the appointment will result in being a no-show appointment

columns.name: EncounterEpicCsn
columns.description: Epic contact serial number (CSN) of the visit. This column identifies patient (EPT) contacts.

columns.name: CoverageFinancialClass
columns.description: Financial class of the coverage; CoverageFinancialClass comes from table CoverageDim, column CoverageFinancialClass by joining on key CoverageKey

columns.name: HospitalAccountEpicId
columns.description: Epic ID of the hospital account associated with the visit. This column identifies account (HAR) records.

columns.name: PrimaryProfessionalAccountEpicId
columns.description: Epic ID of the primary professional account associated with the visit. This column identifies account (HAR) records.

columns.name: MinutesToRoom
columns.description: Number of minutes from the check-in time to the roomed time. By default, this is calculated from CheckInInstant and RoomedInstant.

columns.name: MinutesInRoom
columns.description: Number of minutes from the roomed time to the check-out time. By default, this is calculated from RoomedInstant and VisitEndInstant.

columns.name: Height
columns.description: This column should no longer be used and will be removed in a future version. It has been replaced by HeightInInches. Patient height for the visit. For Epic data, indicators for feet and/or inches might be included.

columns.name: HeightInInches
columns.description: Patient height in inches for the visit. For Epic data, values are only included if the Clarity data is in the format (#' #") and below 9 feet and 12 inches.

columns.name: WeightInOunces
columns.description: Patient weight in ounces for the visit

columns.name: BodyMassIndex
columns.description: Patient body mass index for the visit

columns.name: BodySurfaceArea
columns.description: Patient body surface area for the visit

columns.name: DiastolicBloodPressure
columns.description: Patient diastolic blood pressure for the visit

columns.name: TemperatureInFahrenheit
columns.description: Patient temperature in Fahrenheit for the visit

columns.name: PulseRate
columns.description: Patient pulse rate for the visit

columns.name: RespirationRate
columns.description: Patient respiration rate for the visit

columns.name: TotalCost
columns.description: Total cost associated with the visit

columns.name: DirectCost
columns.description: Direct cost associated with the visit

columns.name: IndirectCost
columns.description: Indirect cost associated with the visit

columns.name: FixedCost
columns.description: Fixed cost associated with the visit

columns.name: VariableCost
columns.description: Variable cost associated with the visit

columns.name: DirectFixedCost
columns.description: Direct fixed cost associated with the visit

columns.name: DirectVariableCost
columns.description: Direct variable cost associated with the visit

columns.name: IndirectFixedCost
columns.description: Indirect fixed cost associated with the visit

columns.name: IndirectVariableCost
columns.description: Indirect variable cost associated with the visit

columns.name: LaborDirectCost
columns.description: Direct labor cost associated with the visit

columns.name: LaborDirectFixedCost
columns.description: Direct fixed labor cost associated with the visit

columns.name: LaborDirectVariableCost
columns.description: Direct variable labor cost associated with the visit

columns.name: SuppliesCost
columns.description: Supplies cost associated with the visit

columns.name: OtherDirectCost
columns.description: Direct other cost associated with the visit

columns.name: OtherDirectFixedCost
columns.description: Direct fixed other cost associated with the visit

columns.name: OtherDirectVariableCost
columns.description: Direct variable other cost associated with the visit

columns.name: Closed
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the visit encounter is closed. This column returns 1 if the visit encounter is closed and 0 if the visit encounter is open.

columns.name: Complete
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the appointment is complete. This column returns 1 if the appointment is complete and 0 if the appointment isn't complete.

columns.name: WalkIn
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the visit encounter is a walk-in. This column returns 1 if the visit encounter is a walk-in and 0 if the visit encounter isn't a walk-in.

columns.name: ReferralRequired
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether a referral is required for the visit. This column returns 1 if a referral is required and 0 if a referral isn't required.

columns.name: TobaccoUseReviewed
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the patient's tobacco use was reviewed during the visit. This column returns 1 if the patient's tobacco use was reviewed and 0 if the patient's tobacco use wasn't reviewed.

columns.name: MedicationsReviewed
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the patient's medications were reviewed during the visit. This column returns 1 if the patient's medications were reviewed and 0 if the patient's medications weren't reviewed.

columns.name: ProblemListReviewed
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the patient's problem list was reviewed during the visit. This column returns 1 if the patient's problem list was reviewed and 0 if the patient's problem list wasn't reviewed.

columns.name: AvsPrinted
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the after visit summary (AVS) was printed for the visit. This column returns 1 if the AVS was printed and 0 if the AVS wasn't printed.

columns.name: AllergiesReviewed
columns.description: 1/0 column that indicates whether the patient's allergies were reviewed during the visit. This column returns 1 if allergies were reviewed and 0 if allergies weren't reviewed.

columns.name: Count
columns.description: Artificial measure on which calculations can be done. The value is 0 for rows marked as deleted, 1 otherwise.

columns.name: AppointmentInstant
columns.description: The date and time of the appointment.

columns.name: CheckInInstant
columns.description: The date and time when the patient was checked in

columns.name: RoomedInstant
columns.description: The date and time when the patient was roomed

columns.name: CheckOutInstant
columns.description: The date and time when the patient was checked out
